1. d4 d5 {[%mdl 32768]} 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 Be7 4. Nf3 Nf6 5. Bg5 h6 6. Bh4 O-O 7. e3 b6 {The Tartakower! This is the backbone of our repertoire. It is a very reliable and dynamic system.} ({I believe it's more interesting than the Lasker with} 7... Ne4 {or the modern line with}) (7... Nbd7) 8. cxd5 {This is White's most straightforward response, but I think we should be happy to face it.} Nxd5 $1 {Very often we will recapture this way, as Black has less space and wants to trade some pieces.} 9. Bxe7 Qxe7 10. Nxd5 {The main move by far. Other moves will transpose to rather harmless lines:} ({A)} 10. Be2 Bb7 {is StartFENrnbq1rk1/p1p1bpp1/1p2pn1p/3p4/2PP3B/2N1PN2/PP3PPP/R2QKB1R w KQ - 0 8EndFEN 8.Be2 Bb7 9.cxd5 Nxd5 10.Bxe7 Qxe7 is a harmless note in the 8.Be2 chapter. [/course/93560/21]}) ({B)} 10. Bd3 Bb7 11. O-O Nd7 {is StartFENrnbq1rk1/p1p1bpp1/1p2pn1p/3p4/2PP3B/2N1PN2/PP3PPP/R2QKB1R w KQ - 0 8EndFEN 8.Bd3 Bb7 9.O-O Nbd7 10.cxd5 Nxd5 11.Bxe7 Qxe7}) ({C)} 10. Rc1 Bb7 {brings us to StartFENrnbq1rk1/p1p1bpp1/1p2pn1p/3p4/2PP3B/2N1PN2/PP3PPP/R2QKB1R w KQ - 0 8EndFEN 8.Rc1 Bb7 9.cxd5 Nxd5 10.Bxe7 Qxe7 .}) 10... exd5 {This is the main position for 8. cxd5. Compared to a normal QGD Exchange, Black's pawn is on b6, not c6, which changes a lot. Black cannot just play ...c6 and ...Bf5 for example, as the c6-pawn would be a serious weakness. If the bishop goes to b7, it would be very passive, and compared to other positions that we will see later, Black does not have the bishop pair to compensate for this. So the right plan is the active ...c5, combined with ...Be6! instead of the more passive ...Bb7.} 11. Rc1 {This is the main line. White hopes to create pressure down the c-file. White can hardly achieve anything without this.} Be6 $1 12. Be2 {A safe move, but not one that puts any pressure on Black.} c5 13. dxc5 bxc5 14. O-O Nd7 15. Qa4 Rfb8 {Black's moves flow naturally. The hanging pawns are well protected and we can create counterplay on the queenside.} 16. Bb5 (16. b3 a5 17. Bb5 Nf6 {is similar.}) 16... a5 17. Bxd7 ({After} 17. Rfd1 Nf6 {Black is doing well, with both ...Ne4 and ...Bg4 in the air.}) 17... Bxd7 18. Qa3 Rb4 {Black has great play on the queenside, and already White must be careful. Bok-Grischuk, Khanty-Mansiysk 2019.} *

