1. d4 d5 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 Be7 4. Nf3 Nf6 5. Bf4 ({For many decades this was just a secondary option for White next to} 5. Bg5 {, but Black's success with the Tartakover, Lasker, and Kramnik variations made life difficult for}) (5. Bg5 {fans, and}) (5. Bf4 {took over. Nowadays it seems clear that}) (5. Bf4 {is more challenging!}) 5... O-O {Now e3 is the top choice by an absolutely huge margin, but other moves have some point and we have to know how to react.} 6. Qc2 {Another typical QGD move if White insists on delaying e3. White does not commit his rook and maintains the options of castling queenside, but the queen is a bit exposed here and Black can often take advantage of this.} c5 $1 {[%mdl 32768] We will meet this the same way as we did with 6.Rc1.} ({A) Once again,} 6... b6 {is inferior, this time because of} 7. cxd5 Nxd5 {the thematic move, but it doesn't work well here. ( 7...exd5 8.e3 is a nice edge for White).} 8. Nxd5 Qxd5 9. e4 $1 {makes 6.Qc2 look quite clever. One point is that} Bb4+ {does not cause the trouble it seems to, as} 10. Kd1 $1 {is good for White - Black will waste a lot of time retreating his pieces.}) ({B) Black should also skip} 6... Nbd7 {because} 7. cxd5 {forces} exd5 8. e3 {with another good exchange variation for White.}) ({C) Finally,} 6... dxc4 {can be met with} 7. e3 $1 {rather than 7.e4 Nc6!}) 7. dxc5 Na6 $1 {A good flexible move. We may recapture on c5, while ...Nb4 is also a possibility. If} (7... Bxc5 8. e3 Nc6 9. a3 Qa5 10. Rd1 {we have been tricked into White's best line in the 6.e3 c5 complex. The less common}) (7... Qa5 {is given by Ntirlis. This seems fine as well, but White has a lot of choice here and it can be a bit complicated after} 8. Nd2 {!?} Qxc5 9. e3 Nc6 10. a3 e5 11. Bg5) 8. Rd1 Qa5 {This active move forces White to display some accuracy.} 9. cxd5 Nb4 $1 ({Instead} 9... Nxd5 10. Bd6 {transposes to the note 8.cxd5 Nxd5.}) 10. Qa4 {White rather desperately exchanges queens.} Qxa4 11. Nxa4 Ne4 $1 {Threatening mate in one!} 12. e3 Nxd5 {We will take on c5 next with an easy position.} *

