1. d4 d5 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 Be7 4. Nf3 Nf6 5. Bf4 ({For many decades this was just a secondary option for White next to} 5. Bg5 {, but Black's success with the Tartakover, Lasker, and Kramnik variations made life difficult for}) (5. Bg5 {fans, and}) (5. Bf4 {took over. Nowadays it seems clear that}) (5. Bf4 {is more challenging!}) 5... O-O 6. e3 b6 7. cxd5 {Finally we come to the most popular move. This is a common reaction against any setup with ...d5 and ...b6, be it a Queen's Gambit Declined or a Queen's Indian Defence.} Nxd5 $1 ({Preferable to} 7... exd5 {, as we know Black is happy to trade some pieces.}) 8. Nxd5 Qxd5 {The most active move, but it offers up a pawn.} (8... exd5 {is better than it was last move, as Black is happy to have exchanged knights.} 9. Bd3 c5 {is doubtless playable, but I prefer to only allow this structure if White has made some concession, as we saw in the 7.a3 line.}) 9. Be2 {This modest looking move is not so simple to deal with.} Qa5+ {[%mdl 32768] This was a novelty when Ntirlis suggested it back in 2018. Now it looks like Black's most reliable move. The downside is that it can easily lead to an endgame where for the most part Black is just looking to prove a draw.} (9... c5 $2 10. Ne5 {with Bf3 coming, is not the way for Black.}) (9... Bb4+ $6 {is also misguided} 10. Nd2 Bxd2+ 11. Qxd2 Qxg2 {is just too risky after} 12. O-O-O {.}) (9... Ba6 {is what we would like to play, and Anand tried this once.} 10. Bxc7 $1 Qa5+ 11. Kf1 Bxe2+ 12. Qxe2 Nd7 {gives Black some compensation, but I don't think it's enough.} 13. h3 Rac8 14. Bg3 Rc6 15. Kg1 Rfc8 16. Kh2 Rc2 17. Qd3 {was Karjakin - Anand, Saint Louis 2019. Although Anand managed to hold, I do not see this as an improvement on the main line.}) 10. Nd2 Ba6 11. O-O c5 12. dxc5 {This is risky, but we have to know how to meet it.} Rd8 $1 13. Bd6 {No choice.} Bxd6 14. cxd6 (14. Nb3 {does not change anything:} Bxe2 15. Qxe2 Qa6 16. Qxa6 Nxa6 17. cxd6 Rxd6) 14... Rxd6 15. Bxa6 Nxa6 ({We should not try to get cute with} 15... Rxd2 $2 {because of} 16. Qf3 {.}) 16. Qf3 {White has this resource.} Rdd8 {And it's just equal.} *

