 $6 {This is a typical move, but there is a trick here. Note that17.e4?! can and should be met with} Bxd4 $1 (17... Bxd4 {Then after Ne2 c5 White will have to work to get the pawn back. White should prefer the prophylactic 17.Kg2 This is uncommon, but it is a good flexible move. I include it to show that it prevents tactical tricks. 17...Na6 Next we'll play and ...Nb4 and go from there. The position will be similar to many others we'll encounter. Note that White's last move overprotects the f3-bishop, so 17...Bxd4 ?? 18.e3 does not work as we do not have the ...Qf6 trick.}) 18. e3 Qf6 $1 {This hits the f3-bishop. An important point.} *

