1. d4 d5 2. Nf3 Nf6 {[%mdl 32768]} 3. Bg5 {The Torre Attack, in this form, is basically dubious. StartFENrnbqkbnr/pppppppp/8/8/8/8/PPPPPPPP/RNBQKBNR w KQkq - 0 1EndFEN 1.d4 Nf6 2.Nf3 e6 3.Bg5 is more respectable.} Ne4 4. Bf4 {This move is much more sound, although White still needs to be careful.} c5 5. c3 {This is solid, but White is still struggling to reach equality.} cxd4 ({More accurate than} 5... Qb6 6. Qb3 {or} Nc6 7. e3) 6. cxd4 (6. Bxb8 {is a sad move to make.} Rxb8 7. Qxd4 e6 {! with the idea} 8. Qxa7 $2 Bd7) 6... Qb6 $1 ({Better than} 6... Nc6 7. Nc3 {.}) 7. Qc1 {This demands more knowledge from Black.} Nc6 8. e3 {A natural move, but this makes it easy for us.} Bf5 9. Nc3 e6 $15 {This is a very good Exchange Slav structure for Black. White's queen is poorly placed on the c-file.} *

