 to 12.Bd3.}) (11. Be2 Be6 12. O-O c5 13. dxc5 bxc5 14. Qa4 {14.Rc1 transposes to 12.Be2} Nd7 {for 14...Qb7!? see Bertok-Fischer, Stockholm} 15. Rac1 {again transposes to 15.Be2.}) 11... Be6 $1 12. Be2 ({Now} 12. Qa4 {with the idea} c5 13. Qa3 {, is the main line.}) {A safe move, but not one that puts any pressure on Black.} 12... c5 13. b3 (13. O-O Nd7 14. b3 {amounts to the same thing.}) 13... Nd7 {[%mdl 32768]} 14. O-O a5 $1 15. Bb5 Nf6 16. Ne5 Rfc8 17. Qe2 cxd4 {This allows Black to fight for the c-file.} ({There are decent alternatives, such as} 17... Rc7) ({and} 17... Bf5) 18. exd4 Qa3 {[%csl Rc1]} 19. Z0 ({This was Uhlmann - Atalik, Dresden 2005. White has to give up the c-file because} 19. Qd2 $6 Ne4 {causes White even bigger problems.}) *

