te's knight But dynamics prevail! White cannot castle. If White tries to bring his queen back to d2 his position will quickly fall apart.} 19. Qd4 {There are other routes too, but ...Rc8 comes no matter what.} Rc8 20. Qd2 Bg4 $1 {[%cal Gg4f3,Gd5d4] Black threatens ...Bxf3 and ...d4, opening up the position completely. White cannot play without a rook.} (20... Qc4 {is good too, but playing this first is much stronger.}) 21. Nd4 Qc4 $1 {[%cal Gc4c1] There is no real defense to ...Qc1+.} 22. Nb3 {White also loses after} (22. Ne2 Bxe2 23. Qxe2 Qb4+ $1 24. Qd2 {or 24.Kd1 Qe4!} Rc1+) 22... a5 $1 {[%cal Ga5a4,Gc4c1] White can resign.} *

