But dynamics prevail! White cannot castle.} 19. Qa3 {The only move.} Qc4 $1 {[%cal Gc4c1][%mdl 32768]} ({We are certainly not going to let White off the hook with} 19... Qxa3 20. bxa3 Rb8 21. O-O {=}) 20. Kd2 {[%cal Gh1c1] White hopes to play Rc1 when he could actually survive.} Qg4 $1 {[%cal Gg4g2] Keep making threats!} ({If} 20... Rc8 $2 21. Nd4 {and Black's initiative is gone.}) 21. Rg1 ({No choice.} 21. Ne1 $2 d4 {is over.}) 21... d4 $1 {A great move! The position opens further and Black's bishop is ready to show its teeth.} 22. Nxd4 Qh4 {[%csl Rf2,Rh2][%cal Gh4h2,Gh4f2] Black is winning.} 23. Re1 ({White loses after} 23. Ke1 Rc8 24. b3 Rc3 $1 {threatening to take on e3.}) 23... Bc4 {[%cal Re1e2,Gh4f2]} ({This is even better than} 23... Qxf2+ 24. Re2 Qf1 25. Nxe6 fxe6 26. Qd6 Kh8 $17 {Timman-Geller, Hilversum 1973.}) 24. f3 Qxh2 {[%cal Gh2g2]} (24... Qf2+ 25. Kd1 Bf1 {is also winning.}) *

