But dynamics prevail! White cannot castle.} 19. Qa3 {The only move.} Qc4 $1 {[%cal Gc4c1]} ({We are certainly not going to let White off the hook with} 19... Qxa3 20. bxa3 Rb8 21. O-O {=}) 20. Qc3 {The best try. At least White won't get checkmated.} Rb8 $1 {[%mdl 32768]} ({This is stronger than} 20... Qxa2 21. O-O Rb8 22. b4) 21. Qxc4 {White cannot fool around.} (21. Nd2 $2 Qxa2 22. O-O Qxb2 {left Black up a healthy passed a-pawn in A.L'Ami-Sharevich, Panevezys 2007, although she did not manage to win.}) 21... dxc4 22. b3 $1 cxb3 23. axb3 Rxb3 {White has survived and can (must, actually) castle now! The engines favor Black and indeed he has whatever chances there are, but White should certainly hold.} *

