1. d4 d5 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 Be7 4. Nf3 Nf6 5. Bg5 h6 6. Bh4 O-O 7. e3 b6 {The Tartakower! This is the backbone of our repertoire. It is a very reliable and dynamic system.} ({I believe it's more interesting than the Lasker with} 7... Ne4 {or the modern line with}) (7... Nbd7) 8. Bd3 {[%cal Gf1d1,Gd1e2,Ga1c1,Ge1g1,Gh4g3] This natural move is the most common overall, but not by much. White intends to develop smoothly with O-O and Qe2, and then he will be free to deploy his rooks however he likes. Often White will play Bh4-g3 to avoid certain exchanges as well. Black can develop his minor pieces easily enough, but then there's the old question - what to do with the queen? Black needs to trade at least one set of minor pieces. This will be attempted with ...Ne4, or perhaps ...Nh5. Pawn exchanges in the center may help too (for example, if White plays cxd5 we react with ...Nxd5, as always). Black just has to be careful that in his eagerness to trade pieces, he does not give White a big lead in development, which may turn into a tangible initiative.} Bb7 ({This is 10 times more popular than} 8... dxc4 9. Bxc4 Bb7 {which transposes to the informational line with} 10. Be2 {dxc4 .}) 9. O-O {By far the main line.} Nbd7 {[%csl Gd8][%mdl 32768] Black has a solid position, but lacks a good square for his queen - quite typical on the QGD in general. Exchanges will help, but White does not have to be so cooperative.} 10. cxd5 {This is unprincipled. Black gets the exchanges he seeks.} Nxd5 11. Bxe7 (11. Bg3 c5 {transposes to 10.Bg3.}) (11. Nxd5 Bxd5 {11...Bxh4 is fine as well, but in general I do not bother with this extra possibility} 12. Bg3 c5 {again transposes to 10.Bg3.}) 11... Qxe7 {[%cal Gc7c5,Gf8d8,Ga8c8] Stockfish already favours Black here! Our play is easy - bring the rooks to the c- and d-files and play ...c5.} 12. Rc1 {This move order gives Black an extra option.} (12. Nxd5 Bxd5 {does not change the nature of the position.}) 12... Nxc3 $146 {An extra possibility.} (12... c5 {transposes to the next variation.}) 13. bxc3 {Does this improve White's structure or make it worse?} ({Perhaps} 13. Rxc3 {is safer, but} c5 {is also nice for Black.}) 13... c5 {[%cal Ga8c8,Gf8d8,Ge6e5] Black will bring his rooks to the center and ...e5 is a strong possibility too.} *

