nals is crazy. 13...Nb4 followed by ...bxc5 is totally winning for Black: -6 according to Stockfish!}) 12... Nc6 {[%mdl 32768]} 13. dxc5 $2 {[%csl Gb7,Gf6] The h1-a8 diagonal is not open as it was after StartFENrn1q1rk1/pb3pp1/1p3b1p/2pp4/3P4/2N1PN2/PPQ2PPP/2KR1B1R w - c6 0 12EndFEN 12.g4 Nc6 13.dxc5? above, but this is still terrible. There's another bishop on a long diagonal after all!} Nb4 $1 {Just like before, but 'only' -3 or so.} 14. Qb3 bxc5 15. a3 a5 $1 {[%cal Gc5c4] This is a typical idea that comes up in various openings.} 16. axb4 axb4 17. Ne4 Be7 {[%csl Rc1][%cal Gc5c4,Gd8b6] White has an extra piece, but I would not expect him to last long here.} *

