15. Qa3 {Kind of a funny square.} d4 $1 {[%cal Gb7f3] Black seizes the moment.} 16. Bb5 {[%cal Gd1d8,Gb5e8] White is trying to get tricky.} Bxf3 {[%mdl 32768]} 17. gxf3 Re6 {Black is quite comfortable here as White's king looks unsafe.} 18. Bc4 {Relatively best.} ({If} 18. exd4 $2 Bxd4 {White has no way to exploit the pin and his kingside is a wreck.}) 18... Rd6 19. Ne4 Nxe4 20. fxe4 Be5 {This looks nice for Black. White must tread carefully.} 21. exd4 ({White cannot play} 21. f4 $2 dxe3 $1) 21... Rxd4 {The engine calls this equal and I'm sure it is, but I prefer Black with his safer king and better pawn structure. The opposite colored bishops and d5-square for White's bishop allow him to hold the balance though.} ({Another way is} 21... Qg5+ 22. Kh1 Qh5 {but this is unclear after} 23. f4 Bxf4 24. Rd2) *

