1. d4 d5 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 Be7 4. Nf3 Nf6 5. Bg5 h6 6. Bh4 O-O 7. e3 b6 {The Tartakower! This is the backbone of our repertoire. It is a very reliable and dynamic system.} ({I believe it's more interesting than the Lasker with} 7... Ne4 {or the modern line with}) (7... Nbd7) 8. Rc1 {This is a good, flexible move. It may transpose to other lines, but there are independent ideas as well.} Bb7 9. Bd3 {This has no independent significance for us.} dxc4 {[%mdl 32768]} 10. Bxc4 Nbd7 {This is considered via the move order 9.Be2 dxc4 10.Bxc4.} *

