ience.} 16. Bg3 $1 {White will use the bishop to try to cause some problems. This move also sets a trap that could be easy to miss.} (16. f3 $2 Nxa4 {is a free pawn}) (16. b3 Nfe4 {trades pieces and gives Black a fine position.}) 16... Nfe4 $1 ({It looks like White overlooked that his pawn was attacked, but after} 16... Nxa4 $2 17. Ncb5 $1 {threatens to win an exchange with either Nc7 or Nd6, and after} axb5 18. Bxb5 {the black queen will not find a safe refuge.}) 17. Nxe4 Nxe4 18. Bc7 $1 {[%csl Rb6]} ({Sharp play.} 18. Be5 Bf6 19. Bxf6 Nxf6 {and ...Qe7, is easy equality.}) 18... Qxa4 {We have to go for it.} 19. Bxb6 Qb4 {Black must be careful here, as White is fully mobilized.} (19... Rfc8 $2 {was played in Popchev-Delchev, Sofia 1989. Here} 20. Nxe6 $1 {works out well for White.}) 20. Bc7 {The only square for the bishop, but it sets up a threat!} Bd8 $1 {[%csl Gc7][%cal Gb4e7] We know we are happy to exchange these bishops, but this move importantly creates a retreat for our queen!} ({After} 20... Rfc8 $2 {White shows his teeth with} 21. Bxe6 $1 fxe6 22. Rc4 {and our poor queen is trapped!}) ({Black could play} 20... Bf6 {but after} 21. f3 {precision is required.} Rfc8 $1 {21...Nc5? 22.Ba2! threatens Rc4 and causes problems} 22. Nxe6 Bxb2 $13 {is messy, but} 23. Rb1 Nc3 24. Qxb2 Qxc4 {seems to hold everything together.}) 21. Bf4 (21. Bg3 Nxg3 22. hxg3 Bf6 $15 {is just the bishop pair for nothing.}) (21. Bxd8 Rfxd8 {is just equal.}) 21... Bf6 {[%cal Ge6e5][%mdl 32768] Threatening ...e5.} 22. f3 e5 $1 {Anyway.} 23. fxe4 exf4 24. exf4 {[%cal Gf3e4,Ge3f4] White's e- and f-pawns have switched places! White is up a pawn for the moment, but our active bishops allow us to grab the initiative.} Qb6 {[%cal Gb6g1]} 25. e5 {The best choice.} ({The alternatives} 25. Qf2 $2 Bxe4) ({and} 25. Qe3 $6 Rad8 26. Nf5 Qxe3+ 27. Nxe3 Bd4 $17 {are simply worse for White.}) 25... Rad8 $1 26. Qf2 (26. exf6 Rxd4 {Black is fine, as we will take the f6-pawn in short order.}) 26... Be7 {[%cal Ge7c5]} 27. Nb3 {The only move.} Qb4 $13 {[%csl Rb3,Gb7,Rc4,Ge7] We have plenty of compensation here, and it is White who must be careful.} *

