1. d4 d5 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 Be7 4. Nf3 Nf6 5. Bg5 h6 6. Bh4 O-O 7. e3 b6 {The Tartakower! This is the backbone of our repertoire. It is a very reliable and dynamic system.} ({I believe it's more interesting than the Lasker with} 7... Ne4 {or the modern line with}) (7... Nbd7) 8. Rc1 {This is a good, flexible move. It may transpose to other lines, but there are independent ideas as well.} Bb7 9. Bxf6 {Now that Black has brought the bishop to b7, White fixes the pawn structure. We saw this in the main lines of 8.Be2.} Bxf6 10. cxd5 exd5 11. b4 ({Now White can go in two completely different directions - he can continue to develop with} 11. Bd3 {, hoping to be better placed to break with e3-e4 than he was in the lines with the bishop on e2; or he can play}) (11. b4 {, looking to restrain Black's queenside pawns. According the engines, Black can play} c5 {against either move here. There is certain logic to that approach, as White is not castled yet. Indeed, it would be simpler to consider that approach, but I don't think Black is bound to it, and we will attempt to keep things a bit more complicated.}) 11... c6 {With this move Black keeps the game interesting.} 12. Be2 {Of course this is similar to StartFENrnbq1rk1/p1p1bpp1/1p2pn1p/3p4/2PP3B/2N1PN2/PP3PPP/R2QKB1R w KQ - 0 8EndFEN 8.Be2 Bb7 9.Bxf6 Bxf6 10.cxd5 exd5 11.b4 c6 , and 12.Rc1 reaches this position.} Re8 {[%mdl 32768] I think this is the most accurate, but moves like 12...Nd7 and 12...Qd6 have been played too.} 13. O-O Qd6 $1 {Timing is important here.} (13... a5 $6 14. b5 c5 15. Na4 $1 c4 16. Ne5 $1 {causes tactical problems.}) (13... Nd7 14. Qb3 a5 $6 {does not seem to work.} 15. b5 c5 16. Nxd5 Bxd4 {We saw this idea in the 8.Be2 line, but here White has} 17. Bc4 $16 {because compared to the analogous position, the rook is not attacked on a1.}) 14. Qb3 Nd7 15. Rfd1 a5 $1 {Only now.} 16. b5 ({If} 16. a3 {it's a good time for} axb4 17. axb4 b5 {and ...Nb6-c4.}) ({We are also not worried about} 16. bxa5 Rxa5 17. a4 {when we have the usual assortment of ideas. I like} Bd8 $5 {heading for c7.}) 16... c5 {Black has active play. See the illustrative game Brattain-Tang, Saint Louis 2018.} *

