 Rd4][%cal Gc8b7,Ge8c8,Ga8d8,Gd8d4,Gf6d4,Gc6d4] Developing this way, followed by castling long and even ...Rd6 and ...Rhd8 will bring White to a critical position quickly.} (10... O-O {is much more common, but this is even stronger.}) 11. Qc3 Bb7 12. Be2 O-O-O 13. O-O-O {[%cal Gd1d2,Gh1d1]} ({If} 13. Rd1 $2 Rd7 $17 {Black doubles rooks and the d4-pawn is in trouble.}) 13... g5 $5 {[%csl Rd4][%cal Bg5g4] Black has good counterplay as the d4-pawn is weak.} *

