by Bu Xiangzhi.} c5 $146 {[%mdl 32768] An idea of Kornev, which is again in the spirit of the Grunfeld.} ({Alternatives are} 10... Nd7 11. O-O c5 {-Colovic}) ({and} 10... Bb7 11. O-O Nd7 12. Rfd1 a6 13. a4 c5 14. d5 {Black is probably ok here with some care, but White has achieved what he wants - a slight pull - and Bu Xiangzhi has shown that it's not completely harmless.}) 11. dxc5 Ba6 $1 12. Qe4 ({Instead} 12. Qa4 Bxc3+ 13. bxc3 Bxe2 14. Kxe2 Nd7 15. cxb6 axb6 $15 {is similar.}) 12... Bxc3+ 13. bxc3 Bxe2 14. Kxe2 ({White avoids the greedy} 14. Qxa8 Qd3) 14... Nd7 15. cxb6 ({After} 15. c6 $2 Nc5 {the advanced c-pawn won't last.}) 15... axb6 $13 {[%csl Ra2,Rc3,Re2][%cal Gd8c7,Gd7c5] This looks a lot like some lines of the Grunfeld. The open a- and c-file give Black excellent compensation against White's split pawns.} *

