768] I like this active move a lot.} (11... bxc6 {is ok too, and this is similar to the 8.Qb3 line, but here White's queen is a bit safer on c2.} 12. O-O Rb8 13. Rac1 c5 14. Rfd1 {and now the following game is a cautionary tale:} Qe7 $6 {This does not look like the right spot for the queen. a5 or c7 look like better choices.} 15. b3 Bb7 16. Ne4 Rfd8 17. Be2 Bxe4 18. Qxe4 $14 {and White had long lasting advantage in Anton Guijarro - Nakamura, Caleta 2017.}) 12. Nxe5 ({After} 12. Be2 Nxc6 {Black just has the bishop pair for nothing.}) 12... Bxe5 13. cxb7 $6 {Very greedy! And bad...} Bxb7 {[%cal Gb7g2,Ge5h2]} 14. O-O Qc7 $146 {[%cal Ge5h2,Gc7c4]} ({I like this even better than immediately regaining the pawn with} 14... Bxh2+ 15. Kxh2 Qc7+) 15. f4 Qxc4 (15... Bf6 {is also good.}) 16. fxe5 Qc5 {[%csl Re3,Re5] Black will regain the pawn with an edge. Better minor piece, better pawn structure.} *

