 , but it's not considered to be a critical test.} 9. a3 {This move is fairly common, but it was not mentioned by Colovic. In any case, it's not very good. I am repeating myself, but development is important!} Nfe4 $1 {[%mdl 32768] Initiating action.} 10. Be5 {It's not ideal to move a developed piece again, but other moves are worse.} (10. Be2 Bf6 {further increases the pressure.}) (10. Nxe4 {opens the position for Black better developed army.} dxe4 11. Nd2 {or 11.Rd1 Bd7 12.Nd2 Ba4 13.b3 Bc6 $17} f6 $1 12. Nxe4 Nxe4 13. Qxe4 Qa5+ 14. Ke2 e5 15. Bg3 Rd8 {is clearly a lot of play for a pawn.}) 10... Nxc3 11. Qxc3 {[%csl Rg7]} ({White has a change of heart, as} 11. Bxc3 Bd7 $17 {with ...Ba4 and ...Rc8 ideas causes familiar problems.}) 11... f6 $1 12. Bd4 Ne4 13. Qc2 e5 $1 {It's clear that things have gone wrong for White.} 14. cxd5 exd4 15. Qxe4 dxe3 {[%cal Ge7c5,Gf8e8] With ...Re8 and ...Bc5 coming, White will be lucky to survive.} *

