1. d4 d5 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 Be7 4. Nf3 Nf6 5. Bf4 ({For many decades this was just a secondary option for White next to} 5. Bg5 {, but Black's success with the Tartakover, Lasker, and Kramnik variations made life difficult for}) (5. Bg5 {fans, and}) (5. Bf4 {took over. Nowadays it seems clear that}) (5. Bf4 {is more challenging!}) 5... O-O 6. e3 {By far White's main move.} b6 {[%mdl 32768] Our repertoire choice. Other moves were covered in the introductory infomational line.} 7. Qc2 {[%cal Ga1d1] This is not so common, but it's a typical QGD move and it scores well.} Ba6 $1 {[%csl Rc4] Casual development leaves Black cramped, so we play this active move to get some exchanges in.} (7... Bb7 {is doubtless playable, but after} 8. Rd1 {it's not easy for Black. If} Nbd7 9. cxd5 {we must mind the c7-pawn, and} exd5 10. Bd3 {is a typical edge for White.}) (7... c5 {is better, and only slightly favouring White after} 8. dxc5 bxc5 9. Be2 {This is similar to the line with 6.a3 b6 7.e3, but here White has not burned a tempo on a3.}) 8. cxd5 Nxd5 ({Preventing White from castling with} 8... Bxf1 {looks more natural, but} 9. Kxf1 Nxd5 10. h4 $1 {with the idea Ng5 gives White interesting chances.}) 9. Bxa6 Nxa6 {Black should not have any particular problems here. We'll trade another set of pieces, and achieving ...c5 should not be difficult.} 10. O-O ({White can also play} 10. Rd1 Nab4 $1 11. Qb3 {when both} a5 {as played in L'Ami - Haslinger, Germany 2014 and the Ntirlis suggestion 11...Qc8 intending ...c5 look ok.}) 10... c5 11. Rfd1 Nab4 $1 {[%csl Rc2] Black gains a tempo to improve the knight.} 12. Qb3 Nxf4 (12... Qc8 {also looks fine, when ...c4 and ...Nd3 is a possibility.}) 13. exf4 Qc7 $1 {[%csl Rf4][%cal Gc5c4] This hits the f4-pawn while ...c4 is again a strong strategic idea.} 14. dxc5 ({If} 14. g3 $6 c4 $1 {is very nice for Black.}) 14... Bxc5 15. Z0 ({Black is fine. One game continued} 15. Ne5 Rad8 $1 16. a3 Nc6 17. Nb5 Qc8 $1 18. Qf3 {(If 18.Nxc6 Qxc6 19.Nxa7 Qc7 hits the knight and the f4-pawn.)} Nxe5 19. fxe5 f6 $132 {and Black had strong counterplay in L'Ami - Bruzon Batista, Merida 2015.}) *

