1. d4 d5 {[%mdl 32768]} 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 Be7 4. cxd5 exd5 5. Bf4 c6 6. Qc2 {[%cal Rc8f5]} Nf6 7. h3 ({White wants to avoid} 7. e3 Nh5 {but this gives us the tempo we need to bring out the c8-bishop.}) 7... g6 {[%cal Gc8f5]} 8. e3 Bf5 9. Qd2 (9. Bd3 Bxd3 10. Qxd3 O-O {just gives us a normal position.}) (9. Qb3 {is well met by} Qb6) 9... h5 $5 {This move has a bad rap due to White's victory in Carlsen - Aronian. Usually Black seeks to exchange knights on e4. This gives Black more room for his pieces, but White's knights may step on each other a bit, so I like this idea of restricting White's expansion.} ({I looked at} 9... Nbd7 10. Nge2 Ne4 11. Nxe4 Bxe4 $146 {and now} 12. Nc3 $146 O-O {I also rejected 12...Bf5 13.g4 Be6 14.Bd3 h5 15.O-O-O !} 13. O-O-O Bf5 14. g4 {and White looks to be ahead.}) ({The immediate} 9... Ne4 {was Colovic's choice.} 10. Nxe4 Bxe4 11. Ne2 $1 {looks the most challenging. White's structure is very flexible, and he can castle on either side.}) 10. Bd3 {Carlsen's idea - White exchanges bishops now that Black has softened up his kingside a bit.} ({Instead} 10. Nf3 {is now well met with} Ne4 11. Nxe4 Bxe4) ({while} 10. Nge2 h4 $1 {restricts the e2-knigh, showing show another point to Black's pawn advance.}) 10... Bxd3 11. Qxd3 Nbd7 {[%cal Ge8g8] Black can play pretty normally with ...0-0 and ...Re8. If White castles long we can quickly advance on the queenside.} 12. Nge2 {This keeps open the possibility of f3 and e3-e4 (or even g4).} (12. Nf3 O-O {= is fairly straightforward.}) 12... O-O {It may seems risky to castle with ...h5 played, but White can hardly castle long.} (12... a5 $6 {was Aronian's choice. This is a standard enough move to hold up a minority attack, and it is useful if White castles long, but it will look irrelevant if White plays in the center.} 13. O-O O-O 14. f3 $1 b5 15. e4 dxe4 16. fxe4 Nc5 17. Qf3 Ne6 18. Be3 $16 {was Carlsen - Aronian, Wijk aan Zee 2012.}) (12... h4 $5 {could be tried though.}) 13. O-O-O $6 {The engines are disgusted by this move, but a human may go for it!} b5 $1 {[%cal Gd7b6,Gb6c4,Gd8a5,Gb5b4] Black is faster here.} 14. g4 ({If} 14. f3 $6 Qa5 15. Kb1 $2 b4) 14... h4 $17 {[%cal Gd8a5,Gd7b6,Gb6c4] The kingside remains closed and Black's queenside play is easy.} *

