 Black can play normally. ...Nb6 and ...Bd6 is one idea.} 14. f3 h4 $5 {[%csl Re2][%cal Rg2g4] Restricting White's knight, and any g4 ideas.} ({Black could also try} 14... b5 $5 15. e4 b4 {with some ideas like ...dxe4 and ...Nc5, but opening the f-file is a bit risky.}) 15. e4 Nf8 {[%cal Gf8e6,Gf6h5]} ({The immediate} 15... Nh5 $5 {is also possible, even though it drops a pawn. After 16.exd5 Nxf4 17.Nxf4 Bf6 18.dxc6 bxc6 when the computer is perfectly happy with Black's compensation.}) ({After} 15... Nf8 {our knights can head to h5 and e6. We keep the f-file closed. If 16.e5 Nh5 17.Be3 Ne6 18.f4 Nhg7 and our knights will be great on e6 and f5.}) *

