1. d4 d5 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 Be7 4. cxd5 exd5 5. Bf4 c6 {[%mdl 32768]} 6. Qc2 {[%cal Rc8f5]} Nf6 7. e3 ({White does not want to spend time on} 7. h3 {, but he can't have everything.}) 7... Nh5 $1 {[%cal Gh5f4] A very important move. We cannot just let White play h3, Bd3, Nf3 with a secure edge.} 8. Be5 Nd7 {[%cal Gd7e5]} (8... f6 {is not fatal, but it is clearly weakening. Both} 9. Bg3 {and 9.Bxb8 Rxb8 10.Be2 are better for White.}) 9. Be2 {If White does not do this, Black will take on e5 and play ...g6, rerouting the knight to g7.} Nxe5 10. dxe5 {[%csl Rh5]} g6 {[%cal Gh5g7] No choice.} 11. Bxh5 gxh5 {[%csl Gc8,Ge7][%cal Gf7f6] This may look ugly, but it's quite an interesting line for Black. The pawns are not as weak as they seem, and the bishop pair has a ton of potential. A quick ...f6 will open the position. White must try to make something of his slight development lead and in fact he will also generally seek to open things up with an e4 break. Both sides will have to make decisions regarding where to put their king...} 12. Nge2 {This was played by Firouzja successfully against Giri in 2020, but the Black could not complain about the opening.} f6 13. exf6 Bxf6 {[%cal Ge8g8,Gf6g7,Gc8f5,Gh5h4] Black has a lot of active possibilities, so White generally tries to cause problems before Black can consolidate.} 14. O-O-O $6 {This is too risky.} O-O {[%cal Gf6g7,Gc8f5] Black simply wants to play ...Bg7 and ... Bf5 when the bishops will gaze across the board at the white king.} (14... O-O {Rad1 and we have transposed to 14.Rd1.}) 15. e4 {White fights in the center. This is logical, but surprisingly Black can practically ignore it.} Bg7 $1 {[%cal Gf8f2,Ge4d5,Gc8f5] Attacking the f2-pawn.} 16. f4 ({If} 16. exd5 $2 Rxf2 {( 16...Bf5 is good too.)} 17. dxc6 Qe7 {is basically winning for Black.}) 16... Kh8 $5 {[%cal Gb7b5] The king cannot be bothered here, so it's useful to get off of the a2-g8 diagonal.} 17. exd5 (17. e5 {removes all pressure in the center. We just go} b5 {with a free attack.}) 17... Bf5 $17 {[%csl Gf5,Gg7][%cal Gd8e7] The bishops reign supreme and White's king is going to come under attack.} *

