le} 19. Rd2 Rae8 20. f4 c5 21. e5 Kh8 $1 {avoiding checks} 22. exf6 Re3 {with ...d3 coming next, and a mess which of course the engines call equal.}) 17. Nxd4 Bg4 $1 {[%cal Ga8d8]} 18. f3 Rad8 $1 {Black has a powerful initiative. White has to be careful just to survive. Let's check some possibilities.} 19. Qc4+ ({After} 19. Nce2 Be6 $1 {Black threatens ...c5 and White's queenside pawns are under fire.}) 19... Kh8 20. Na4 ({If} 20. fxg4 $2 Bxd4 {White's king will never find peace.}) 20... Qc7 21. O-O ({After} 21. fxg4 b5 $1 22. Qxc6 {instead 22.Nxb5? Bh4+ leads to mate!} Qf4 {and White will not last long.}) 21... Qf4 $1 {[%cal Gf4e3,Gf6d4]} 22. fxg4 Bxd4+ 23. Kh1 Be5 $1 {Threatening mate on h2, while White has back rank problems.} 24. g3 Qxg4 {[%csl Ra4][%cal Gb7b5,Gh5h4] White has survived, but Black is more active and has some advantage.} *

