 $2 18. Qxh5+) 18. f4 ({If} 18. Qxh4 Rg8+ 19. Kh1 {we could take on e6, but} Qf5 $1 {looks even stronger. The obvious} 20. f4 $2 {runs into} Rg4 $1 21. Qh6 Bf8 22. Qh3 Rg1+ {winning the queen So 20.Qf4 is forced. 20...Qxf4 21.exf4 f5 with a big advantage for Black.}) 18... Qh5 {[%cal Gf6f5] We'd love to cut off the e6-pawn with ...f5.} 19. f5 O-O-O $13 {[%csl Ge6,Gf5,Rh3][%cal Gh8g8] The position is quite a mess. White's f5- and e6-pawns looks very strong, but f5 requires constant protection. The white queen covers it, but still looks kind of stuck on h3.} *

