Black has to be accurate here.} Qf4+ 21. Kb1 Raf8 $5 ({This looks simpler than} 21... b6 {which has been has been seen in practice in both Dreev-Grischuk, Apatity 2011 and Vakhidov-Kasimdzhanov, Tashkent 2016.}) 22. Nc5+ Kc8 {And managed to 'castle' long after all!} 23. Nd3 Qf5 {We can go into the endgame.} 24. Qxf5+ Rxf5 25. Nxe5 Rxe5 26. Rxd4 Rf8 {[%csl Rf2,Rf3][%cal Gf8f7] The endgame should not be difficult despite the pawn deficit.} *

