several times, but it looks strange to me. I see now reason why we cannot follow the script with} Kf8 $146) 11... Kf8 $5 {[%cal Gf8g8,Gd7f8][%mdl 32768] This is a Big Idea. The moves of the h-pawns have inconvenienced both sides. We do not really need to castle, but we want to find good squares for out pieces. We can go to g8 to prepare a possible ...Nf8-e6, and we also clear the way for a future ...Ra8-e8.} ({Instead} 11... Nf8 12. Bg5 {is a bit annoying now as the h5-pawn becomes a target.}) 12. O-O Kg8 $1 {[%cal Gd7f8]} ({An improvement on} 12... Nb6 $6 {which was played in Moiseenko-Jojua, Dresden 2010. Here} 13. a4 $1 a5 14. Qb3 {is typically annoying.}) 13. Bg5 (13. Qb3 {can me met with} Qb6) 13... Ne8 $1 {[%csl Rh4][%cal Ge8d6] Another point of Black's play - the knight will come to d6 and White's h4-pawn is weak.} *

