1. d4 d5 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 Be7 4. cxd5 exd5 5. Bf4 c6 6. e3 Bf5 7. g4 Be6 8. h3 {[%cal Gf1d3,Gd1c2] White is satisfied with chasing off Black's bishop and now looks to consolidate his space advantage and develop normally with Bd3, Qc2, Nge2, O-O-O and so on.} (8. Bd3 {This will generally transpose to the 8.h3 line.} Nd7 9. h3 {and we are in the 8.h3 line. White can vary with a couple of questionable moves. 9.Qf3?! g5 10.Bg3 Ngf6 11.h3 h5 is already favoring Black. 9.Bf5?! is another strange move. 9...Bxf5 10.gxf5 Ngf6 Black develops normally.}) 8... Nd7 {[%cal Gg7g5,Gh7h5] We develop a piece and await White's next move. Black will not be idle - the thematic ...h5 and ...g5. strikes are the source of counterplay.} 9. Bd3 {The main line. White can bring the knight to either f3 or e2 if we are idle, but we won't be.} h5 {This is a big alternative, which was Colovic's choice. We will consider this as an informational line. I decided to go with 9...g5, both for variety and because I slightly prefer it. It is also consistent with our (necessary) answer to 9.Nf3.} 10. gxh5 Ngf6 ({There is also} 10... Ndf6 {when White has tried seven different responses!}) 11. h6 g6 {[%cal Gf6h5] Black intends ...Nh5 to eventually round up the h6-pawn.} 12. Qc2 Nh5 13. Bh2 Rxh6 14. O-O-O Ng7 {[%cal Ge6f5] Colovic's choice.} ({I may prefer} 14... Ndf6 {with ideas like the typical ...Bd6 , or possibly ...Ne4!? , an idea we'll see later.}) {One line that concerned me is:} 15. Kb1 Bf5 16. Bxf5 Nxf5 17. e4 dxe4 18. d5 {[%csl Re8] This makes me a bit nervous. White has some initiative in the center, and our king is still stuck.} Qb6 {[%cal Gb6c6,Ge8c8]} 19. d6 Bf6 20. Nxe4 O-O-O {Colovic was happy with Black here, as his pawn structure is good and he has managed to evacuated his king from the center. That d6-pawn cuts through the position though and I think White can make use of his initiative.} 21. Nxf6 Nxf6 22. Nf3 $1 {[%cal Gf3g5] Coming to g5.} Rxh3 23. Ng5 Rxh2 {Forced.} 24. Rxh2 Nxd6 25. Qc3 {Black has eliminated the d6-pawn and is technically ok on material, but White's rooks have range and the g5-knight is annoying. We could go further but Stockfish is at about +.5 here.} *

