1. d4 d5 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 Be7 4. cxd5 exd5 5. Bf4 c6 6. e3 Bf5 7. g4 Be6 8. h4 Nd7 {This is the most popular move by far.} ({Colovic gives} 8... Bxh4 {and considers it a refutation. I don't want to debate this, but I will say that 8.h4 is still being played a lot, and black players are rarely grabbing the pawn. I am not aware of any theoretical problems with the pawn grab, but I imagine that players of the QGD simply do not find it to be practical - there is a lot of memorization and the position ultimately should probably end up in a draw. The line goes 9.Qb3 g5 10.Be5 f6 11.Bh2 Bxg4 when 12.Qxb7 should ultimately leads to a perpetual check (which is fine theoretically if you remember it all) while 12.Be2 (which I consider to be more critical) leads to an endgame where Black is a pawn up, but with a really bad pawn structure.}) 9. h5 {This is the older way of playing. White simply gains space.} Nh6 $1 {[%csl Rg4][%cal Gf7f5] A very original idea which is considered standard now. Karpov played in against Kasparov in their 1985 match, and its value was upheld in many games by QGD experts Vaganian and Lputian.} ({After} 9... Ngf6 10. f3 $16 {Black is very cramped on the kingside.}) 10. f3 {White protects the g4-pawn so that he can develop, but it's one more pawn move, and Black is ready to fight for the initiative.} f5 {[%mdl 32768]} 11. Bxh6 {This is a better version for White, but it's still not dangerous.} (11. gxf5 {is even worse.} Bh4+ 12. Kd2 Nxf5 {and White's position looks ridiculous.}) 11... gxh6 12. gxf5 Bxf5 {[%cal Ge7h4] White's position look smore exposed than Black's.} 13. Bd3 {Looking to eliminate one of Black's bishops.} Bh4+ 14. Ke2 Bxd3+ 15. Qxd3 ({The computer prefers} 15. Kxd3 {racing to c2 . 15...Rg8 16.Kc2 Qe7=}) 15... Qe7 {[%cal Ge8c8] Black is ready to castle long and bring his rooks into play. White's position has little margin of error, for example} 16. Z0 (16. f4 {looking to plug things up with Nf3-e5.} Rg8 17. Kd2 $6 {Better was 17.Nf3 Rg2+ 18.Kd1 Bf6=} Rg2+ 18. Nge2 Bf2 19. Rh3 $6 O-O-O {$17 White is all tied up and ...Nf6 and ...Re8 are coming.}) *

