for lack of space.}) 12. hxg6 {White really must take.} hxg6 {[%cal Gg6g5,Gf7f5][%mdl 32768] Black has clear counterplay and has done very well in practice.} 13. Bg3 $2 {This was played in Nakamura - Aronian, Sao Paulo/Bilbao 2011. White won, but the move is actually a peculiar blunder!} Nxg4 $1 14. Bxg4 Qd7 $17 {[%csl Rh3] Very unusual! The h3-knight is essentially trapped. Black wins back the piece and remains up material. note that 15.f3 f5 does not really help.} *

