he bishop has nothing to do on this diagonal.} Bb7 {intending ...Nbd7 and ...c5, is already more comfortable for Black.}) 9... Nbd7 {[%cal Gc7c5,Gd7c5,Gc8b7] Black will play ...Bb7 and ...c5.} ({I prefer this move order to} 9... Bb7 {when} 10. a3 {intending b4 forces our hand.} c5 11. dxc5 Bxc5 12. Qxd8 Rxd8 {is still fine, but we can be more ambitious.}) 10. e4 $6 {This does not take advantage of our move order finesse.} Bb7 {[%csl Re4][%cal Gb5b4,Gc7c5]} ({This is better than} 10... b4 {when} 11. e5 $1 {equalizes for White.}) 11. e5 Nd5 $15 {[%cal Gc7c5] ...c5 is coming next.} *

