po kicking us away.}) 13. Nc3 {It is important to shield the c-file.} Nbd5 {[%cal Gc7c5] Black is ready for ...c5. White can only aspire for something if he can hold off this advance.} ({If you want to get off the beaten track,} 13... Qe8 $5 {is an idea, getting off of the d-file to prepare ...c5.}) 14. Ne5 $6 {Too soft.} c5 $15 {[%cal Gc8c1][%mdl 32768] Black is already better.} 15. Nxd5 Bxd5 16. Bxd5 (16. dxc5 Rxc5 {intending ...Qa8 is great for Black.}) 16... exd5 $1 {[%cal Gc5c4] A very rare case where Black will recapture this way. Here ...c4 would give Black a big strategic advantage, so White is compelled to take.} 17. dxc5 Bxc5 {[%csl Rc1][%cal Gc5f2,Gf6e4,Gf8e8,Gg7g5,Gc8c1] Black rarely goes for an isolated queen's pawn in these lines, but here the initiative flows easily. The engine already claims that Black has a winning advantage!} 18. Qb1 Ne4 19. Nd3 Bb6 $17 {[%csl Ra1,Rb1,Rf2,Rg1][%cal Gf8e8,Gd8f6,Gg7g5] White is all bottled up and Black's moves are easy to play.} *

