there are ideas like ...Qa8, ...Nbd7, ...Be4, and finally ...c5. Anand played this move quite a bit. There is a lot of subtle maneuvering with} 11. Rc1 Be4 12. Qb3 Nc6 13. e3 Qa8 14. Qd1 {going on.}) 11. Qc1 {[%csl Rc5][%cal Gc7c5] White has to keep an eye on the c5-square.} c6 $5 {[%cal Gb8d7,Gc6c5,Ye4f3,Yd8d4] This unusual move happens to be the engine's top choice! It was quickly dismissed by Avrukh in his classic Catalan repertoire book for White, but he almost cryptically pointed out that he could be wrong! This little move first got serious attention in the game Giri-Kramnik, London 2014, and it was also featured in Jan Gustafsson's Chess24 course. The engine also considers 11... Nc6, as well as the unusual 11...Bd5, and even 11...h6 as 'equal' before even getting to the natural looking 11...Nbd7.} ({And then there's the most popular move} 11... Bb7 $5 {This line is fine, I think, but for starters White can repeat moves with} 12. Qc2 {.}) 12. a4 {This is a serious move, typical of the Catalan.} Nbd7 {Let's develop.} ({This is certainly not a position where Black can grab the pawn.} 12... Bxf3 $2 13. Bxf3 Qxd4 14. axb5 {with pins everywhere.}) ({I would also avoid} 12... b4 {for reasons given in the Informational line.}) 13. Nc3 {White should maintain the tension.} ({After} 13. axb5 {both recaptures are fine. I like to capture towards the center myself, so let's say} axb5 {.}) 13... Bg6 {[%cal Ga8c8] With the knight on c3 I prefer this retreat. If ( 13...Bd5 14.Qc2 and the d5-bishop is uncomfortable.} 14. Nh4 {This is a better try.} Bh5 $1 {[%mdl 32768] Black can leave the c6-pawn to its fate. White should not take it though.} 15. Bxc6 $6 b4 $1 {[%cal Ga8c8] Now if the knight moves, ...Rc8 will create a deadly pin.} ({The immediate} 15... Rc8 $2 16. axb5 {does not work for Black.}) 16. Bxa8 bxc3 17. Bf3 {This is the best try.} (17. Qxc3 Qxa8 $17 {is great for Black. The light-squared bishop is strong.}) 17... cxd2 18. Qxd2 Bxf3 19. Nxf3 a5 $1 {[%csl Ya4,Yb2,Gb4][%cal Ge7b4,Gf6e4,Gd8a8] This seals up the queenside. White is ok on material, but Black's minor pieces have good squares.} *

