1. d4 d5 2. c4 e6 3. Nf3 Nf6 4. g3 {The Catalan! This is a very popular and serious choice. We will go for a very classical line. There is a lot to know, but it's interesting and common sense will help guide you in most lines if you forget something.} Be7 5. Bg2 O-O 6. O-O ({By far the main move. We will also check} 6. Qc2 {and}) (6. Nc3 {.}) 6... dxc4 ({This is the classical setup. Black can also play the Closed Catalan with} 6... c6 {.}) 7. Qc2 {This is White's main move by far, simply intending Qxc4.} ({The big alternative is} 7. Ne5) 7... a6 8. a4 ({This has been more popular than} 8. Qxc4 {in recent years. White discourages ...b5, which we saw allowed Black to immediately develop his problem c8-bishop with ...b5 and ...Bb7. The move of the a-pawn also gains some space, but it noticeably weakens the b4-square.}) 8... Bd7 {[%cal Gd7c6] This move looks a little funny at first, but it is by far Black's top choice. The bishop gets to the long diagonal after all.} ({There are other moves too, like} 8... Nc6) ({and} 8... c5 {, but Black has trouble reaching equality in these lines.}) 9. Qxc4 {This is unsurprisingly the main line, but there are other moves too, which we will consider later.} Bc6 10. Bg5 ({This is the most popular move. We will consider} 10. Bf4 {and other moves in later chapters.}) 10... Bd5 11. Qc2 ({There are two main lines here:} 11. Qc2 {and}) (11. Qd3 {, which can lead to very different kinds of play.}) 11... Be4 {[%mdl 32768]} 12. Qc4 ({The c2-square is a good spot for White's queen so we continue the chase. Now} 12. Qc1 {is the main line, while}) (12. Qd1 {is also seen often enough. Other moves are rare and not dangerous.}) {Ok, so White is repeating move. Very ambitious...} 12... Bd5 {We repeat. I know many players believe that their opponents stay up all night preparing drawing lines with White, but it does not really happen so much.} ({If you want to play on, there is Gustafsson's suggestion} 12... Nc6 $5 {which puts some pressure on the d4-pawn and prepares ...Na5 and perhaps ...c5. This is also approved by Stockfish. Here is one possibility:} 13. e3 Na5 14. Qc3 c5 $1 15. dxc5 Rc8 16. b4 h6 $1 {and the complications work out well for Black.}) *

