the game Romanishin-Beliavsky, Belgrade 2000.} Bxf6 {and Black should win back the pawn soon.}) 14. Nbd2 {The other game that dissuaded me from 12...c5 went} (14. Qxd8 Rxd8 15. Nbd2 Bc6 16. Nb3 Be7 17. Na5 $14 {Nakamura-Anand, Saint Louis 2015.}) 14... Bc6 15. Ne5 Bxg2 16. Kxg2 $14 {This may not look like much, but Black kept suffering and eventually succumbed in Giri-Leko, Baku 2015.} *

