e will see a lot of, but with the white knight on f3 instead of c3.} 16. Qb3 {White tries to bother us with a direct attack on b7.} Nc6 $1 ({Black has played} 16... Ra7 {here, but it's not necessary.}) {Attacking the d4-pawn and of course the usual ...Nb4 is a possibility.} 17. Qxb7 Nxd4 18. Nxd4 Qxd4 {[%csl Rb2,Rc7][%cal Ga8b8] Black need not fear any two rooks vs. queen situations as the black queen is very active and the rooks do not have targets.} 19. Qxa8 $6 {Tempting perhaps, but mistaken.} Rxa8 20. Bxa8 Qc4 $5 {[%cal Gc4e2,Gf6b2] This is considered very advantageous for Black by the engines.} ({The natural} 20... Qxb2 {is good too.}) *

