t we will check a couple of little tactical details.} 17. h4 $6 {This is a typical move, but there is a trick here.} ({Note that} 17. e4 $6 {can and should be met with} Bxd4 {Then after} 18. Ne2 c5 $15 {White will have to work to get the pawn back.}) ({White should prefer the prophylactic} 17. Kg2 {This is uncommon, but it is a good flexible move. I include it to show that it prevents tactical tricks.} Na6 {Next we'll play and ...Nb4 and go from there. The position will be similar to many others we'll encounter. Note that White's last move overprotects the f3-bishop, so 17...Bxd4?? 18.e3 does not work as we do not have the ...Qf6 trick.}) 17... Bxd4 $1 18. e3 Qf6 $1 {[%cal Gf6f3] This hits the f3-bishop. An important point.} *

