 obvious move is a good alternative.} 15. Qxc6 Qd6 $1 16. Qf3 {White does not want to improve Black's pawn structure, so this is the only choice.} Rfb8 17. e4 {[%cal Ge4e5,Gd4d5] White has to try to be active to prove compensation.} (17. Ra4 $2 Rxa4 18. Nxa4 Qb4 $17 {loses a pawn for nothing.}) (17. d5 {is too hasty.} exd5 18. Nxd5 Nxd5 19. Rxd5 Qe6 $15 {again with an extra pawn.}) 17... Qc6 18. d5 Qd7 $146 ({Avoiding the trick} 18... exd5 $2 19. e5) 19. dxe6 Qxe6 {[%csl Rb2,Gb4,Gb8,Gc4,Ge6] White has fought for the light squares, but it's not easy for him to develop. Black's position still looks easier to me.} *

