15 {Black immediately seizes the initiative.}) ({Instead} 15. Rxb4 {looks wrong.} Bxb4 {hits the a5-pawn and plans the typical ...Bxc3 and ...Qd5. After} 16. Bg5 Bxc3 {avoiding 16...Bxa5?! 17.Ne4!} 17. Qxc3 Qd5 18. Bxf6 gxf6 {Black is at least ok, for example} 19. Rc1 Rb8) 15... Rxa4 16. Qxa4 Qb8 {[%cal Gb8b5,Gb8b3] The established response, but there are some other decent moves.} ({One that I like is} 16... h6 $5 {Black waits for White to take a pawn and then ...Qd5 comes. Stockfish even likes 16...h5!? haha!} 17. Qxc4 {or 17.Qxc6 Qd5 18.Qxc7 Bd8=} Qd5 18. Qxd5 cxd5) 17. Qxc4 ({If} 17. Nc3 $6 Qb3 {intending ...Bb4 is better for Black.}) 17... Qb7 $1 {[%cal Gf8b8]} ({Black avoids the obvious} 17... Qb5 18. Qxb5 $1 cxb5 19. Be3 Nd5 20. Rc1 $14 {intending Rc6, with some light pressure.}) 18. b4 Qb5 $1 {Only now! The point can be seen after:} 19. Qxb5 cxb5 $132 {[%csl Rb4][%cal Gf6d5] White's b4-pawn is a target.} *

