wn sacrifice scores much better than 13.e4. It's not objectively superior, but it's tricky.} exd5 {[%mdl 32768]} 14. Nxd5 $2 {This simple recapture is a bit naive and not in line with White's previous play. I can't imagine that any white player will get this far just to play this way, but you never know.} Bxd5 15. Rxd5 Nc6 {[%cal Gc6b4] Black completes development, makes a threat, and is still up a good pawn.} 16. Rc5 {The only way to make any threats. Without this move White could resign. Still, it's not enough.} Nb4 {This is the simplest.} (16... Na5 {is also very strong.}) 17. Qd2 c3 $1 {[%csl Gb4] Interfering with the white queen's attack on our knight.} 18. bxc3 Qe7 $1 {[%csl Rc5][%cal Ge7c5,Ga8d8] This quite awkward for White to meet.} *

