a1!? is tempting, although 22.Rxa1 Bxa1 23.h4 $132 gives White counterplay.}) 20... Qxb2 21. Qxb2 Bxb2 22. Rxa6 Rxa6 23. bxa6 c3 {[%cal Gc3c2,Ga6a7] Both rooks should soon vanish from the board.} *

