wn sacrifice scores much better than 13.e4. It's not objectively superior, but it's tricky.} exd5 14. Nd4 $1 {The crux of White's play.} Qe5 $1 {An important centralization!} ({Black must resist the urge to exchange pieces too quickly. After} 14... Bxd4 $6 15. Rxd4 {White has great compensation as the d5-pawn will fall and Black is still not getting developed. If} Nd7 $2 16. Nxd5 Bxd5 17. Bxd5 Rd8 18. axb5 axb5 19. Bc6 {with a deadly pin.}) 15. e4 $1 (15. Nxc6 $2 {is against the spirit of the line, which is based on hampering Black's development.} Nxc6 {intending ...Nb4 is good for Black. White can take on d5 but he'll still be down a pawn with a worse position. For example} 16. axb5 {or 16.Nxd5 Rad8 $17} axb5 17. Rxa8 Rxa8 18. Nxd5 Rb8 $17) 15... dxe4 16. Nxe4 {The critical move.} Bxe4 $5 {This leads to complications and will be our main line.} (16... Ra7 {is fairly safe. This will be considered as an alternative.}) 17. Bxe4 Ra7 {Now White can capture on either b5 or h7.} 18. Nf3 $5 {White could take on h7 immediately too. 18.Bxh7+ Kh8 19.Nf3 Qxb2 transposes.} Qxb2 $1 ({An improvement over} 18... Qe7 $2 19. Bxh7+ Kh8 20. Rd5 $1 {with the idea Rh5 After} g6 21. Re1 {White was winning in B.Jacobson-Khamrakulov, New York 2019. If} Qb4 22. Bxg6) 19. Bxh7+ Kh8 20. Qf5 {[%cal Gf5h5] Threatening Qh5.} g6 {Forced.} 21. Qc5 {[%csl Ra7,Rf8][%cal Gc5a7,Gc5f8] An unusual double attack, hitting both black rooks in their own camp.} Bg7 {[%mdl 32768]} 22. Qxa7 Qf6 $1 {[%csl Rf3][%cal Gf6f3,Rh7g6,Gf7g6] White will not be able to take on g6 yet as then the pressure on the f-file would be too much.} ({After} 22... Kxh7 23. Qxc7 {Black has trouble activating his knight.}) 23. Nd4 ({Instead} 23. Kg2 Qc6 $1 {leaves White tangled up.}) 23... Nc6 {Finally bringing the knight out - to trade it off.} 24. Nxc6 Qxc6 25. axb5 axb5 {Ands we are finally ready to take the bishop, so White grabs the pawn.} 26. Bxg6 fxg6 $13 {[%csl Gb5,Gc4,Gc7] Black is the exchange down, but the queenside pawns are strong. The engines calls it equal, but it looks more fun for Black.} *

