1. d4 d5 2. c4 e6 3. Nf3 Nf6 4. g3 {The Catalan! This is a very popular and serious choice. We will go for a very classical line. There is a lot to know, but it's interesting and common sense will help guide you in most lines if you forget something.} Be7 5. Bg2 O-O 6. O-O ({By far the main move. We will also check} 6. Qc2 {and}) (6. Nc3 {.}) 6... dxc4 ({This is the classical setup. Black can also play the Closed Catalan with} 6... c6 {.}) 7. Qc2 {This is White's main move by far, simply intending Qxc4.} ({The big alternative is} 7. Ne5) 7... a6 8. a4 Bd7 9. Ne5 {This is an obvious move to make, especially if one is not particularly well-versed in the theory of the line. It's pretty easy to neutralize though - if you know how to play.} Bc6 10. Nxc6 Nxc6 {[%csl Rd4] White has grabbed the bishop pair, but it's cost him some time. The d4-pawn is now under attack, so White's choices are limited.} 11. Bxc6 {Tempting perhaps, but White scores poorly.} bxc6 {If we compare this position with the one arising after 9.Rd1 Bc6 10.Nc3 Bxf3 11.Bxf3 Nc6 12.Bxc6 bxc6, we see that White is not only missing the moves Rd1 and Nc3! I suppose White could argue that Nb1-c3 interferes with recouping the c4-pawn, but it's still a couple of tempi and White has to work to equalize here.} 12. Rd1 {So White is down both Nb1-c3 and the move.} Qd5 $1 {[%mdl 32768]} 13. Na3 {White understandably would like his pawn back.} (13. Nc3 $2 {is a poor move. After} Qh5 $17 {Black remains a pawn up and he is much more active. White's kingside is weak and ...Ng4 is already a concern. There's also the typical active moves ...c5 and ...Rfb8 to consider.}) 13... c5 $5 {First we break down the center.} ({Even here} 13... Qh5 {is a viable alternative.}) 14. dxc5 Qh5 {[%cal Gf6g4]} 15. Nxc4 {Everyone has avoided this is practice, as ...Ng4 looks scary. White is not yet worse though.} Ng4 16. h4 Bxh4 $5 {This forces White to find a draw.} ({Both} 16... Qxc5) ({and} 16... Bxc5 {are fine too. Black has split queenside pawns, but his pieces are active.}) 17. Ne3 $1 {The only move.} (17. gxh4 $2 Qxh4 {gives Black a strong attack.}) 17... Bxg3 18. Nxg4 Qxg4 19. fxg3 Qxg3+ {Black will deliver perpetual check.} *

