nd advantage.}) 16. bxc4 b5 17. Z0 ({This liquidates the queenside and we get an equal position. Unfortunately we are not winning a pawn, for example} 17. axb5 axb5 18. Bb2 bxc4 {when White can pester our rook with Bd4 and win back the pawn with moves like Ra4, Rfc1, etc.}) *

