st circumstances, and the knight is needed on the queenside. Instead} 16... Bxc5 17. Rd1 $1 Qe7 18. Qxb7 a5 19. Bd2 $16 {pressures the a5-pawn and gives White a big advantage.}) 17. Ba3 {This is the most common, but it just leads to a drawn position.} (17. Qxb7 Nxc5 {is also equal. We have ...Rb8 and ...Nb3 coming to eliminate White's bishop pair.}) 17... Nxc5 18. Bxc5 Bxc5 19. Qxb7 a5 {[%cal Gc5b4] And we have simple equality.} *

