must play actively! Typical ideas include ...Bh3 as well as ...Qh5 and ...Ng4. But first we will nudge the white queen from her active post.} ({Later we will also check} 13. Nc3) 13... Be6 14. Qc2 {[%csl Rc7][%cal Gc1f4] Now 15.Bf2 is a threat. Black always has to watch out for this.} Bf5 (14... Bh3 {is also possible, but why not drive the queen to an awkward square first?}) (14... Nd5 $5 {was recommended by Jon Ludvig Hammer in his Chess24 course. Black prevents Bf4, and ...Nb4 is a possibility. This has hardly been played if you're looking to experiment or absolutely must avoid a repetition.}) 15. Qd2 {[%csl Rc1][%cal Gd2f4,Gd2g5] This locks in the bishop, but White plans for this to be a temporary problem, as Qf4 or Qg5 may come soon.} ({After} 15. Qc4 Be6 {White can repeat or go for Qd3 this time around. In turn, Black can play with 14...Bh3 or Hammer's 14...Nd5}) 15... Bh3 {This is the most forcing, and it sets a few traps based on White's weak back rank. Sometimes White will play f3 and Rf2, so we avoid that.} ({Black should avoid} 15... Rad8 $6 16. Qf4 $1) ({We checked} 15... Rfe8 {, simply attacking the e2-pawn, as an alternative.}) 16. Re1 ({This is universally played - the e-pawn needs protection.} 16. Rd1 Rfe8 {seizes the initiative.} 17. Nc3 Ne4 18. Qe3 Nxc3 19. bxc3 Qh5 {and Black wins back the pawn while maintaining pressure.}) 16... Rad8 17. Qe3 {[%csl Gc1] White offers an exchange of queens while freeing up his queenside.} Qd5 $1 {[%csl Rg2][%mdl 32768]} ({An important move. Instead} 17... Qh5 $6 18. f3 $1 {transposes to a bad line we'll see in the 14.Qd3 variation.}) 18. f3 ({If} 18. Qf3 $2 Qd1 {ends the game.}) 18... Ng4 $1 19. Qc3 {[%cal Gc1f4,Ge2e4] Freeing the c1-bishop and possibly preparing e4 to get some breathing space. White must be careful with this though.} (19. Qxa7 $4 {is too greedy.} Rfe8 {threatens ...Rxe2, and after} 20. Nc3 Qxf3 {wins.}) 19... Rfe8 20. e4 $2 {Too hasty.} Qb7 {[%cal Gb7b6]} 21. Na3 $2 ({Or} 21. fxg4 Rxe4) 21... Ne5 {[%csl Rf3][%cal Gd8d3] Black has an overwhelming initiative.} *

