1. d4 d5 2. c4 e6 3. Nf3 Nf6 4. g3 {The Catalan! This is a very popular and serious choice. We will go for a very classical line. There is a lot to know, but it's interesting and common sense will help guide you in most lines if you forget something.} Be7 5. Bg2 O-O 6. O-O ({By far the main move. We will also check} 6. Qc2 {and}) (6. Nc3 {.}) 6... dxc4 ({This is the classical setup. Black can also play the Closed Catalan with} 6... c6 {.}) 7. Ne5 Nc6 {This is a surprising move if one is unfamiliar with it. Black voluntarily allows his structure to be compromised. We have seen in other lines that tripled c-pawns are not always so bad. The main point is that Black is developing quickly, especially considering that White has just moved his knight for a second time. Now White's choice is limited because his d4-pawn is under attack. Both captures on c6 lead to interesting play. The only real alternative is 7...c5 which is very solid but not very interesting. After} 8. Bxc6 ({dxc5 Qc7} 8. Nxc4 {Qxc5 Black can probably gradually equalize, but there are fewer opportunities for counterplay.}) 8... bxc6 9. Nxc6 Qe8 10. Nxe7+ Qxe7 11. b3 {[%cal Gc1a3] This move is uncommon and it scores poorly, but it is not bad at all. It was recommended by Ipatov in his book Unconventional Approaches to Modern Chess.} Rd8 {[%cal Gd8d1] We will take on b3, but this move is also good and scores well. Black has to memorize some stuff and ultimately it leads to a lot of simplifications.} 12. bxc4 ({Worse is} 12. Ba3 $6 Qd7 13. bxc4 Ba6 $15 {when White's pawns are weak.}) 12... Qd7 {[%csl Rd4]} ({Avoiding} 12... c5 $6 13. Ba3) 13. Bg5 ({After} 13. Nc3 Bb7 $132 {is best, intending ...Qc6 This is better than 13...Qxd4?! 14.Be3 $14 Yanayt-A.Jacobsen 2019}) 13... c5 $1 {[%cal Gc8a6] This move was not in Ipatov's book. Play becomes rather forced.} ({Ipatov gave the line} 13... Qxd4 14. Na3 $1 Ba6 {This too is probably not best.} 15. Qxd4 Rxd4 16. f3 $14 {with an edge for White. Black cannot take on c4 because of Be3.}) 14. Bxf6 (14. d5 Ba6 15. Nc3 Bxc4 16. Bxf6 gxf6 {amounts to the same thing.}) 14... gxf6 15. d5 Ba6 16. Nc3 Bxc4 17. Ne4 ({If} 17. dxe6 Qxe6 {intending Ne4 looks fine; but not 17...fxe6? 18.Qc2 $16}) 17... Kg7 18. d6 Bd5 19. Nxc5 Qxd6 20. Qd4 Rac8 {Black is fine here.} *

