1. d4 d5 2. c4 e6 3. Nf3 Nf6 4. g3 {The Catalan! This is a very popular and serious choice. We will go for a very classical line. There is a lot to know, but it's interesting and common sense will help guide you in most lines if you forget something.} Be7 5. Bg2 O-O 6. O-O ({By far the main move. We will also check} 6. Qc2 {and}) (6. Nc3 {.}) 6... dxc4 ({This is the classical setup. Black can also play the Closed Catalan with} 6... c6 {.}) 7. Ne5 Nc6 {This is a surprising move if one is unfamiliar with it. Black voluntarily allows his structure to be compromised. We have seen in other lines that tripled c-pawns are not always so bad. The main point is that Black is developing quickly, especially considering that White has just moved his knight for a second time. Now White's choice is limited because his d4-pawn is under attack. Both captures on c6 lead to interesting play. The only real alternative is 7...c5 which is very solid but not very interesting. After} 8. Nxc6 ({dxc5 Qc7} 8. Nxc4 {Qxc5 Black can probably gradually equalize, but there are fewer opportunities for counterplay.}) ({This is almost as popular as} 8. Bxc6 {White is not looking to grab a pawn at the cost of his Catalan bishop. Instead he pins his hopes on the strength of this bishop and his apparently superior pawn structure.}) 8... bxc6 {[%csl Gc4,Gc6,Gc7][%cal Ga8b8,Gf6d5,Gc8a6,Gc6c5][%mdl 32768] Another line with triple isolated pawns. In exchange for this ugly structure, Black finds it relatively easy to be active.} 9. e4 $2 {[%csl Rg2]} ({Moves other than} 9. Na3 {are not so common and are not very dangerous. Black's moves tend to be easy to find and active.}) {This is totally inconsistent. White blocks his bishop. White's center is not imposing at all, as the pawns are certain no threat to advance.} 9... e5 $5 {Direct and aggressive.} ({Black is spoiled for choice.} 9... Rb8 $17 {is simple, and good as well.}) 10. dxe5 {There's not much else.} (10. Be3 $2 Ng4 {is a disaster.}) (10. d5 $6 cxd5 11. exd5 Rb8 $17 {is great for Black as well.}) 10... Qxd1 11. Rxd1 Ng4 $17 {[%cal Gg4e5,Ge7c5] Black has a strong initiative.} *

