en in Lenderman-Tang, Philadelphia 2016.}) 12. Rd1 {[%csl Gd4] White gives the d-pawn some extra protection.} Rb6 {[%mdl 32768]} (12... Qc8 {intending ...Rd8 is playable as well.}) 13. a4 {[%cal Gc1a3]} (13. Qa5 $6 {is mistimed. After} Bb5 {White can forget about} 14. a4 {because of} Ra6) 13... Qd6 {[%cal Rc1a3,Gf8b8,Gf6d5]} 14. Qa5 $6 {Again, bad timing. White should play this at move 12.} Nd5 15. e4 Qb4 $1 16. Bd2 {Damage control.} (16. Qxb4 $2 {is even worse.} Nxb4 17. Bf4 Nd3 18. Bxc7 Rb2 $17 {was Iturrizaga Bonelli - Dominguez Perez, Internet 2018. The c4-pawn is strong and Black's knight dominates.}) 16... c3 17. Qxb4 Rxb4 18. Be1 Nb6 19. Bxc3 Rxa4 $15 {[%csl Ga4,Ga6,Gb6,Rg2] White has managed to eliminate the frontal c-pawn and Black's remaining doubled pawns may not impresses, but Black does remain a pawn up. His pieces are more active too.} *

