1. d4 d5 2. c4 e6 3. Nf3 Nf6 4. g3 {The Catalan! This is a very popular and serious choice. We will go for a very classical line. There is a lot to know, but it's interesting and common sense will help guide you in most lines if you forget something.} Be7 5. Bg2 O-O 6. O-O ({By far the main move. We will also check} 6. Qc2 {and}) (6. Nc3 {.}) 6... dxc4 ({This is the classical setup. Black can also play the Closed Catalan with} 6... c6 {.}) 7. Na3 {A maximalist approach. White aims to recover the pawn. while developing a piece and But we can take this piece, and hold the pawn...} Bxa3 {We cannot let White regain the pawn with no concessions.} 8. bxa3 {[%csl Ga2,Ga3,Gc4] We have an in interesting strategic situation. White has the bishop pair, but a pawn less and doubled a-pawns.} Bd7 {[%cal Gd7c6] A familiar strategy. We cannot fianchetto the bishop properly, so we look to bring the bishop to the long diagonal another way.} 9. Ne5 {This has always been the main line of 7.Na3, and it's always been considered to be just fine for Black.} Bc6 10. Nxc6 {White has to go for this, but it helps us develop.} Nxc6 11. Bb2 {The main line.} Nd5 {[%cal Gd5b6,Gc4c3,Gf7f5][%mdl 32768] The knight is strong here, and it can go to b6 to protect the c4-pawn. White will also have to watch for ...c3 now.} ({Originally I planned to recommend} 11... Qd6 $5 {which worked well in the old game Alburt-Geller, New York 1990, but after some digging I ultimately decided to go with the most popular continuation.}) 12. Rb1 $6 {This has been played a lot, but it's not very good.} (12. e3 $2 {is just silly.} c3 13. Bc1 Qd6 $17) 12... f5 $1 {[%csl Gd5][%cal Gb7b5] Maintaining the knight on its strong square and planning ...b5.} ({More often Black has gone for the typical moves} 12... Nb6 {and}) (12... Qd6 {, but}) (12... f5 {is strong.}) 13. a4 (13. Ba1 Rb8 {amounts to the same thing.}) 13... a6 14. Ba1 Rb8 {Whtie can't stop ...b5.} 15. Rc1 b5 16. axb5 axb5 17. a4 {Fortunately for White, he has multiple a-pawns to fight with.} Na5 $1 {Greed is good.} 18. axb5 Qd7 $15 {[%csl Ga5,Gd5][%cal Gd7b5] Black has kept the extra pawn and his knights are as strong as White's bishops.} *

