 well.} ({The alternative} 9... Nxd5 10. Qxc5 Bxc5 {is much improved over the endgame above and probably equal, but White's play is easier and he scores well in practice.}) 10. O-O Nc6 {[%csl Rc3][%cal Ge6e5,Gd5h5]} 11. Qd2 {The most common move in practice. White really wants that endgame!} (11. Bf4 {can be met with} Qh5 {but I like 11...Qb5! , hitting the e2-pawn, even more.}) 11... Rd8 $1 {Only on our terms.} ({If} 11... Qh5 12. Qg5 {is very insistent, although Black is fine here as well.}) 12. Nc3 Qa5 $1 {[%csl Rd2][%cal Ge6e5][%mdl 32768] White's queen is forced to move yet again, and we will play ...e5 next with a great game.} ({Again} 12... Qh5 {would allow White to play the safe} 13. Qg5) *

