s hoping for.}) 10. Qb3 {The most logical.} e5 $1 {[%cal Gb4d5,Gc8e6][%mdl 32768] The point of Black's play. We are actually making room for ...Be6.} 11. Nc2 {This is considered best by the engine, at least at first.} Nbxd5 {[%cal Gc8e6]} ({Simplest.} 11... Nfxd5 {looks fine too.}) 12. Nc3 Nxc3 13. Qxc3 e4 $1 {[%cal Gc8g4,Gd8d5,Gd5h5] The pawn may look potentially weak here, but Black is active enough that it won't be a problem.} 14. Be3 Qd5 $1 {[%cal Gd5h5]} 15. Bd4 Qh5 {[%csl Re2,Rh2][%cal Gf6g4,Gc8g4,Gc8h3] Black is doing well here as he has clear play on the kingside.} 16. Z0 (16. f3 $6 {was played in Khairullin-Riazantsev, Sochi 2015. Now} Be6 $1 17. fxe4 Rac8 18. Qd2 Rfd8 {gives Black fantastic play.}) *

