1. Nf3 {In this chapter we will focus on Reti lines with e3 instead of g3. There was a whole book written on this approach with various move orders - 'e3 Poison' by GM Axel Smith. It's a tricky setup that is not without bite, so I think it's appropriate name.} ({Of course White could start with} 1. c4 {too.} e6 2. Nf3 d5 3. e3 Nf6) 1... d5 2. c4 ({And here} 2. b3 Nf6 3. Bb2 e6 4. e3 {would be another move order.}) 2... e6 3. e3 ({And again White can play} 3. b3 Nf6 4. Bb2 Be7 5. e3 {5.g3 O-O 6.Bg2 b6 is the Neo-Catalan chapter.}) 3... Nf6 {We will pretty much play ...Nf6, ...Be7, and ...O-O against anything. The timing of other moves such as ...c5 and ...b6 will vary a bit, depending on what White does.} 4. b3 ({If White plays} 4. d4 {anytime in the next few moves, we'll just end up in the QGD 4.e3 chapter.}) 4... Be7 {[%mdl 32768]} ({This is consistent with our whole repertoire. Another good setup, recommended by Gustafsson in his Chess24 course, is} 4... c5 5. Bb2 Nc6 6. cxd5 exd5 {when Black will play ...Bd6 instead of ...Be7. This is perfectly sound, but it leaves us hanging against White's 4.Nc3 move order.}) 5. Bb2 O-O {This is the real starting point for this chapter. White's setup is not as harmless as it appears to be.} 6. Be2 {This is popular, and we cannot play in the same way as we do against 6.Nc3. But it's easily diffused, and Black has more than one way to easy equality.} (6. d4 {is yet again the QGD with 4.e3.}) (6. g3 {looks surprising, but it's not bad, and} b6 $1 7. Bg2 Bb7 8. O-O c5 {brings us to the Neo-Catalan.}) 6... c5 7. O-O ({After} 7. cxd5 {we will play} Nxd5 $1 {7...exd5 8.O-O Nc6 9.d4 transposes to 8...exd5, which is what we are avoiding.}) 7... Nc6 {[%cal Gd5d4] Now Black is ready to play ...d4.} 8. d4 cxd4 9. Nxd4 {This is safe - for both colors.} (9. exd4 b6 $1 {is a worse version of the QGD 4.e3 lines for White, as his bishop is passive on e2.}) 9... Nxd4 10. Qxd4 ({Or} 10. Bxd4 dxc4 11. Bxc4 Bd7 {and ...Bc6.}) 10... dxc4 {The simplest.} 11. Qxc4 (11. Bxc4 Qxd4 12. Bxd4 Bd7 {does not change the assesment.}) 11... Bd7 {[%cal Ga8c8,Gd7c6] The bishop will come to c6 soon. It's not super exciting, but if White plays with little ambition we'll just enjoy easy equality and go from there.} *

