ults after} 9. Be2 dxc4 10. Bxc4 Qxd1+ 11. Rxd1 b6 {again copying White's queenside structure.}) 9... dxc4 {[%mdl 32768]} 10. b4 ({This looks smarter than} 10. Bxc4 Na5 $5 {when White may have problems with his b3-pawn.}) 10... Be7 11. Bxc4 Qxd1+ 12. Rxd1 a6 {[%cal Gb7b5,Gc8b7] The position is just equal. We have symmetry and no initiatve for either player. There are a lot of pieces on the board though, so it's a game.} *

