y. Now we have a kind of Tarrasch QGD, which is not what we usually go looking for, but White has played a rather modest setup, and he is still a couple of moves away from getting castled.} Nc6 9. Bb5 {This looks more aggressive than 9.Be2, but two can play that game.} (9. dxc5 Bxc5 10. Be2 {brings us back to 7.d4.}) 9... Bg4 $1 {The pin is annoying for White.} 10. Bxc6 {This is consistent at least.} (10. Be2 {is passive.} Bxf3 11. Bxf3 cxd4 12. exd4 Qd7) 10... bxc6 {[%mdl 32768]} 11. dxc5 Bxc5 12. O-O Re8 {[%csl Rf3][%cal Gd8e7,Gc5d6] It's about equal. White has the better structure, but Black has the bishop pair and attacking chances.} *

