1. Nf3 d5 2. g3 Nf6 3. Bg2 e6 4. O-O Be7 5. d3 {With this move White delays the fight in the center and plays a reversed King's Indian Defence, thus the nomenclature 'King's Indian Attack'.} ({Instead} 5. c4 O-O {and now} 6. b3 {is the Neo-Catalan. 6.d4 is the main line of the Catalan. 6.Qc2 is a peculiar move. After 6...c5 White has nothing better than 7.d4 when we have reached the 6.Qc2 Catalan.}) 5... O-O ({I prefer this move order to} 5... c5 6. e4 $5 {intending Qe2, which can even be followed with e5 and c4!?. If} dxe4 7. dxe4 Qxd1 8. Rxd1 Nxe4 9. Ne5 Nd6 10. Na3 $13 {White has good compensation for the pawn. Now 6.d3 is by far the main move, but we'll also check some rare alternatives.}) 6. Nbd2 c5 ({There are alternatives, such as} 6... b6) ({and Colovic's suggestion} 6... Nc6 {, but we will stick with Black's main setup.}) 7. e4 Nc6 8. Re1 ({This is more accurate than} 8. e5 Nd7 9. Re1 Qc7 $1 {hitting the e5-pawn and forcing} 10. Qe2 b5 11. h4 a5 {which transposes to the line with 10.h4.}) 8... b5 ({Sometimes Black tries} 8... Qc7 {hoping to get White into the position mentioned on the last move, but} 9. c3 $5 {as given by Plichta, causes fresh problems. So we will stick to the main line.}) 9. e5 {Finally we come to the main line.} Nd7 {[%mdl 32768]} 10. h4 $6 {This is a typical move, but it's an inferior move order.} Qc7 $1 {[%csl Rc1,Re5] Hitting the e5-pawn before White is ready for Bf4.} 11. Qe2 a5 12. Nf1 Ba6 {[%cal Ga6e2]} ({It's very logical to play this way with the queen in the bishop's sights. Instead} 12... Bb7 13. Bf4 Rfc8 {is good too. This looks like our main lines but here White has spent a tempo on Qe2.}) 13. Bf4 Rfc8 {[%cal Gc7d8]} 14. Ne3 Qd8 {The typical setup. White has played the rather committal Qe2 and Ne3.} 15. h5 h6 16. Ng4 Bf8 {[%csl Re2][%cal Gb5b4,Ga5a4] This was Bachmann-Mekhitarian, Florianopolis 2022. It's similar to positions we'll see later but Black is in effect up a tempo, as we will see that White's queen should usually be on d2 to support g4-g4 or potential sacrifices on h6.} *

