1. Nf3 d5 2. g3 Nf6 3. Bg2 e6 4. O-O Be7 5. d3 {With this move White delays the fight in the center and plays a reversed King's Indian Defence, thus the nomenclature 'King's Indian Attack'.} ({Instead} 5. c4 O-O {and now} 6. b3 {is the Neo-Catalan. 6.d4 is the main line of the Catalan. 6.Qc2 is a peculiar move. After 6...c5 White has nothing better than 7.d4 when we have reached the 6.Qc2 Catalan.}) 5... O-O ({I prefer this move order to} 5... c5 6. e4 $5 {intending Qe2, which can even be followed with e5 and c4!?. If} dxe4 7. dxe4 Qxd1 8. Rxd1 Nxe4 9. Ne5 Nd6 10. Na3 $13 {White has good compensation for the pawn. Now 6.d3 is by far the main move, but we'll also check some rare alternatives.}) 6. Nbd2 c5 ({There are alternatives, such as} 6... b6) ({and Colovic's suggestion} 6... Nc6 {, but we will stick with Black's main setup.}) 7. e4 Nc6 8. Re1 ({This is more accurate than} 8. e5 Nd7 9. Re1 Qc7 $1 {hitting the e5-pawn and forcing} 10. Qe2 b5 11. h4 a5 {which transposes to the line with 10.h4.}) 8... b5 ({Sometimes Black tries} 8... Qc7 {hoping to get White into the position mentioned on the last move, but} 9. c3 $5 {as given by Plichta, causes fresh problems. So we will stick to the main line.}) 9. e5 Nd7 10. Nf1 {[%cal Gh2h4,Gf1h2,Gf1e3,Gc1f4] White's best move. The knight may come to e3 or h2 and now the e5-pawn can be supported with Bf4.} a5 {This is Black's traditional move.} ({We will be going for the modern} 10... Bb7 {The point is that after} 11. h4 Qc7 12. Bf4 Rfc8 {we are ready to bring the queen back to d8. The f8-square is useful for defenders (bishop, queen, or knight) while Black's rooks are well placed on the queenside.}) 11. h4 Ba6 {[%cal Gb5b4,Ga5a4,Gc1f4,Gf1h2,Gh4h5]} ({Again,} 11... Qc7 {does not work out well because of} 12. Bf4 Ba6 13. Ne3 Rfc8 $2 14. Nxd5) ({The position with} 11... Ba6 {is a big tabiya where White can choose between} 12. N1h2 {, 12.Bf4 , and the immediate 12.h5 For a long time Black was considered to be doing well here, but practice has borne the opposite conclusion, and White scores well over 60% with all three moves.}) *

