1. Nf3 d5 2. g3 Nf6 3. Bg2 e6 4. O-O Be7 5. d3 {With this move White delays the fight in the center and plays a reversed King's Indian Defence, thus the nomenclature 'King's Indian Attack'.} ({Instead} 5. c4 O-O {and now} 6. b3 {is the Neo-Catalan. 6.d4 is the main line of the Catalan. 6.Qc2 is a peculiar move. After 6...c5 White has nothing better than 7.d4 when we have reached the 6.Qc2 Catalan.}) 5... O-O ({I prefer this move order to} 5... c5 6. e4 $5 {intending Qe2, which can even be followed with e5 and c4!?. If} dxe4 7. dxe4 Qxd1 8. Rxd1 Nxe4 9. Ne5 Nd6 10. Na3 $13 {White has good compensation for the pawn. Now 6.d3 is by far the main move, but we'll also check some rare alternatives.}) 6. Nbd2 c5 ({There are alternatives, such as} 6... b6) ({and Colovic's suggestion} 6... Nc6 {, but we will stick with Black's main setup.}) 7. e4 Nc6 8. Re1 ({This is more accurate than} 8. e5 Nd7 9. Re1 Qc7 $1 {hitting the e5-pawn and forcing} 10. Qe2 b5 11. h4 a5 {which transposes to the line with 10.h4.}) 8... b5 ({Sometimes Black tries} 8... Qc7 {hoping to get White into the position mentioned on the last move, but} 9. c3 $5 {as given by Plichta, causes fresh problems. So we will stick to the main line.}) 9. e5 Nd7 10. Nf1 Bb7 ({We checked the traditional move} 10... a5 {as an informational line.}) 11. h4 {[%cal Gc1f4,Gh4h5,Gf1h2,Gh2g4,Gf1e3,Gh5h6,Ga7a5,Ga5a4,Gb5b4,Gd5d4] This is the main line. White has various attacking ideas on the kingside. We will seek our fortune on other parts of the board.} Qc7 {[%csl Gf8][%cal Gf8c8,Gc7d8,Ge7f8,Gd7f8,Gd8f8][%mdl 32768] This is the modern setup. We want to play ...Rfc8 and then the queen goes back to d8. Then the f8-square is available for more effective defenders than the rook - bishop, queen, knight.} 12. Bf4 Rfc8 {[%cal Gc7d8]} 13. Ne3 {[%cal Ge3d5,Ge5e6] This looks too commital. It prepares a trick, but we are in time to dodge it.} Qd8 ({Of course not} 13... a5 $2 14. Nxd5 exd5 15. e6) 14. c4 ({An independent continuation which looks logical with the knight on e3. Instead} 14. Ng4 {transposes to 13.N1h2.}) 14... bxc4 15. dxc4 d4 16. Ng4 Rab8 {[%csl Gd4][%cal Gh4h5,Gh7h6,Gb7a8,Ge7f8,Gb8b2,Yb2b3,Ya7a5,Ya5a4] It's a sharp position, but Black has already made inroads in the center and on the queenside. We'll always meet h5 with ...h6.} 17. Z0 (17. Ng5 Bxg5 $5 18. Bxg5 {( 18.hxg5 looks slow as White is a long ways from using the h-file. 18...Ne7 $132 )} Ne7 $132 {We'll trade light-squared bishops and unpin with ...Qf8.}) *

