dxc4 d4 {The usual reaction.} 17. Ng4 Rab8 {The sacrifices on h6 do not work, so this is a little more accurate than ( 17...Bf8 18.Nd2!? as played in Gukesh-Rafiee, Sitges 2019.} 18. Qd2 ({Both} 18. Bxh6 $2 gxh6 19. Nxh6+ Kg7) ({and} 18. Nxh6+ $2 gxh6 19. Bxh6 Kh8 {lead nowhere.}) (18. Nd2 {could still be played, but then Black would not bother with ...Bf8. Both} Na5 $5 {and 18...Ba8!? 19.b3 a5 give Black clear counterplay.}) 18... Bf8 $132 {[%cal Gb7a8,Ga7a5,Ga5a4] We've seen this structure before. Black is ready to press on the queenside.} *

