e6 {remains quite playable here. Then} 5. e4 {is some kind of French with White's queen on d3.} dxe4 6. Nxe4 Be7 {should be a very satisfactory Burn French.}) 5. e4 cxd4 {Forcing White to move the queen again. He can do so right away, or exchange on f6 first. This will force White to move the queen again.} 6. Qxd4 e5 {And again. Surprisingly, White is ok here if he's careful.} 7. Qa4 $6 {This looks 'active' and it's the only move seen in practice, but White will be worse now.} d4 {Gaining space.} 8. Nd5 Be7 ({Simple, but the untried} 8... Bd6 $5 {looks good too.}) 9. Bxf6 ({After} 9. Nxe7 Qxe7 $15 {Black will just castle and play ...h6 and ...Nc5.}) 9... Bxf6 {White's fourth queen move prevents us from castling.} 10. Qa3 Be7 {[%mdl 32768]} 11. Qxe7+ Qxe7 12. Nxe7 Kxe7 $15 {[%cal Gd7c5,Gc8e6,Ga8c8] Black is a bit better here. More space, better bishop, open c-file.} 13. Z0 ({One game continued} 13. f4 {Probably the only way to avoid being clearly worse.} exf4 14. O-O-O {if 14.Nh3 Ne5 15.Nxf4 Be6 $15} Ne5 15. Rxd4 Be6 $15 {was Karagiannis-Banikas, Ermioni Argolidas 2005.}) *

