1. d4 d5 2. Nc3 Nf6 3. Bg5 {The Veresov. This was never considered to be too dangerous - a little tricky perhaps - but not objectively good. This holds true today, and Black scores very well. Today's engines confirm that Black is doing great. Simply put, the c3-knight is poorly placed as White cannot attack or defend in the center with c4 or c3. So White often plays for e2-e4, but it's not easy to achieve without the weakening move f2-f3.} ({Although it took a long time, nowadays it's considered that Jobava's} 3. Bf4 {is much more challenging. In this case White's c3-knight serves a purpose - to go to b5, hitting the c7-pawn.}) 3... Nbd7 {The main line. We avoid doubled pawns. We will typically play ...e6 and ...c5, often with ...a6 or ... h6 thrown in somewhere. Black has many playable moves.} ({Here} 3... e6 {may look consistent with our repertoire, but after} 4. e4 {we are suddenly in a Classical French! - 1.e4 e6 2.d4 d5 3.Nc3 Nf6 4.Bg5. If this is part of your repertoire, go right ahead and play this way. Black has avoided the popular Steinitz Variation - 1.e4 e6 2.d4 d5 3.Nc3 Nf6 4.e5.}) ({Shankland's suggestion} 3... Bf5 {and}) (3... c6 {are both very solid.}) ({Jones gives the King's Indian style} 3... g6) ({Finally there is the direct} 3... c5 {This, along with our line, are Black's best scoring setups. White has quite a few moves here. They range from bad to harmless. So we do not have much to worry about, and we certainly don't have to know everything in order to confidently face an uncommon and objectively weak line. There are some lines though where we should definitely know a few things.}) 4. f3 {[%cal Ge2e4] White intends to play e4. Of course this move takes away a square from White's g1-knight, and weakens the dark squares.} ({This is the traditional main line, but when it was found to be lacking, White tried to spice things up with another ugly move,} 4. Qd3 {, or else put on the brakes with the more solid}) (4. e3 {or}) (4. Nf3) 4... c6 {[%csl Gd5][%cal Gd8b6,Gd7a5,Ge7e5] This is very solid, but not without ambition. We will see that we are well prepared for White's central advance. We also solidify the d5-pawn, so we can strike with ...e5 if White sits around.} ({Black can also strike immediately with the typical} 4... c5 {or}) (4... h6 5. Bh4 {and then} c5) 5. e4 {I mean, this is the point, right?} ({After the rare} 5. Qd3 e5 {is great for Black.}) ({Sometimes White hesitates with} 5. Qd2 {when} h6 {when is a good answer. After both} 6. Bh4 e5 {and Bf4 Nh5! White is worse.}) 5... dxe4 6. fxe4 e5 $1 {Thematically striking on the dark squares. This position has been seen many times, with Black scoring a huge 65%. Today's engines confirm White's problems.} 7. dxe5 Qa5 $1 {[%cal Ga5e1,Ga5g5,Gf6e4] Threatening ...Nxe4 while preparing ...Nxe5 as well as ...Bb4. The loose bishop on g5 is the tactical justification. This position has been seen dozens of times. Perhaps there was a debate at some point, but today we know that Black is already better.} ({Black is not really worse after} 7... Nxe5 8. Qxd8+ Kxd8 {, highlighting the benign nature of White's concept.}) 8. Bxf6 {This is clearly the main line, but I think it's just bad!} gxf6 9. e6 {White's main try.} Ne5 $1 {[%cal Gc8e6][%mdl 32768] A rare move, but it's very strong. The tempo is worth more than the pawn as we fuel our dark-squared initiative.} ({There is certainly nothing wrong with the common} 9... fxe6 10. Qg4 h5 $1 {when instead of} 11. Qxe6+ Be7 {followed by ...Ne5 White should play 11.Qg6+ Ke7 12.Nf3 Black is still better, but not by as much as he is after 9...Ne5!}) 10. exf7+ Kxf7 {[%cal Gf8a3,Gc8e6] Black is still ready to play all the typical moves.} 11. Qh5+ {White can try to bother our king, but it won't last.} Kg7 {[%cal Ge5d3,Ga5h5] Now we threaten ...Nd3+, winning White's queen.} 12. Qh4 Bb4 {[%cal Gb4c3] Another threat.} 13. Qg3+ ({More queen moves. After} 13. Nge2 Rd8 {White can hardly move.}) 13... Kf7 {[%cal Gh8g8]} 14. O-O-O ({If} 14. Nge2 Rg8 {followed by ...Bg4 is totally winning for Black. White can't get developed.}) 14... Be6 $17 {[%cal Gh8g8,Ga8d8] Black's initiative is hard to slow down.} *

