1. d4 d5 2. Nc3 Nf6 3. Bf4 {This Jobava version is more challenging than the older Veresov with 3.Bg5.} e6 ({A classical response which fits well with our repertoire. Other lines include the direct} 3... c5 {, the prophylactic}) (3... a6 {, and the fianchetto .}) 4. e3 ({White should certainly go for the disruptive} 4. Nb5 {now to justify White's second and third moves.}) {This looks highly questionable.} 4... Bb4 {[%cal Gc7c5,Gd8a5,Gf6e4] This puts a lot of pressure on White. Black is already fighting for an advantage here and his score is close to 60%! It looks a bit like a Winawer French, but White does not have the space advantage or attacking chances that he'll find there.} 5. Bd3 ({Now the only sensible moves are} 5. Nge2 {to avoid doubled pawns, and}) (5. Bd3 {to get developed.}) 5... c5 $1 {Just like in the French.} 6. dxc5 ({After} 6. a3 $2 Bxc3+ 7. bxc3 Qa5 $17 {White will find it rather difficult to avoid losing a pawn.}) 6... Nbd7 {[%cal Gd7c5]} ({This is the most flexible move, but} 6... O-O {is good too.}) 7. Nge2 {This avoids doubled pawns.} a6 $1 {[%csl Rb5][%cal Ge6e5,Ge5e4] A clever move which threatens to play ...e5-e4, winning a piece. White's bishop will not be able to go to b5 now.} 8. a3 {I was familiar with Shankland's analysis when I was faced with this unfamiliar move. It didn't take me long to goof it up.} Bxc5 {[%cal Ge6e5,Ge5e4][%mdl 32768] Again White has to watch out for ...e5-e4.} 9. Bg3 ({If} 9. e4 $6 e5 10. Bg3 {(Not 10.Bg5 Bxf2+! )} d4 $17 {is great for Black. For example} 11. Nd5 {(Or 11.Nb1 Nh5 $17 )} Nxd5 12. exd5 O-O {Bakalchuk-Postny, Tiberias 2016.}) 9... O-O $15 ({Now I was trying to decide between} 9... O-O {,}) (9... Nh5 {, and}) (9... e5 {Ultimately I made the worst choice possible along with a good choice - a draw offer.}) ({Black keeps all options open and has a great position.} 9... e5 $2 {[%cal Gf8e8,Ge6e5,Gb7b5] was agreed drawn here in Canty-Vigorito, Charlotte 2022.} 10. Bf5 $1 {wins a pawn though. It was near the end of a long event and we were both done for the day.}) (9... Nh5 {is fine though.} 10. Nd4 Nxg3 11. hxg3 {White does have the open h-file. The engine still prefers Black slightly after} Nb6 {.}) *

