1. d4 d5 2. Nc3 Nf6 3. Bf4 {This Jobava version is more challenging than the older Veresov with 3.Bg5.} e6 ({A classical response which fits well with our repertoire. Other lines include the direct} 3... c5 {, the prophylactic}) (3... a6 {, and the fianchetto .}) 4. Nb5 {This is much more critical as it forces Black to misplace his knight.} Na6 {[%csl Ra6][%mdl 32768]} 5. e3 Be7 {I just want to get on with development. We can kick White's knight later.} ({The immediate} 5... c6 {is more popular.}) 6. Nf3 O-O {[%cal Gc7c6,Gc6c5,Ga6b4,Gb4c6,Ga6b8,Gb8c6] Black's main plan is to kick the knight with ...c6, and then play ...c5. The a6-knight will often reroute to c6, via b4 or b8.} 7. Be2 {The most common move. We'll start here to get an idea of Black's ideas against calm play.} (7. h3 {does not change anything.} c6 8. Nc3 c5 {We're never afraid of} 9. Bxa6 bxa6 {unless White can play Ne5-c6 immediately.}) (7. a3 {prevents ...Nb4, but after} c6 8. Nc3 c5 {we can still reroute the knight with ...Nb8.}) (7. Bd3 {looks a bit odd.} c6 8. Nc3 Nb4 {now comes with tempo unless White wants to give up the bishop.} 9. Be2 c5) 7... c6 8. Nc3 c5 9. O-O (9. Ne5 {intending to take on a6, would be met with} Nb4 {or 9...Nb8 heading to c6.}) (9. Bxa6 bxa6 {is not a problem. We'll just play ...Bb7 and ...Rc8. The bishop pair is more important than the slight pawn weaknesses.}) 9... Nb4 {[%cal Gb4c6] The knight could go to b8 too; this just looks more disruptive and maybe White will burn a tempo on a2-a3.} 10. Nb5 {This is nothing to worry about but it's nice to know why.} (10. Ne5 Nc6 {looks fine. The c3-knight is oddly placed, as is often the case in the Veresov.}) 10... a6 11. Bc7 ({If} 11. Nc7 $2 Ra7 $17 {and the knight is not getting out.}) 11... Qe8 ({Not} 11... Qd7 $2 12. Ne5 Qe8 13. Nd6 {when White will win an exchange.}) 12. Nd6 Qd7 13. Nxc8 Qxc7 14. Nxe7+ Qxe7 {This was Rodriguez Vila-Fier, Florianopolis 2019. It's level, and I'd be quite happy with Black. Plenty of space and an imbalance with the minor pieces. Black won a long game.} *

