 ({White's king will have trouble finding a safe haven, and his rooks do not come into the game very easily. For example} 18. Qe2 e5 19. Bg3 Qe6 {eyeing the g4- and a2-pawns.}) ({Stockfish comes up with the following amusing line:} 18. g5 e5 19. Bg3 hxg5 20. h6 g6 21. h7+ Kh8 22. Qd7 $1 {Wait, what?!} Qxd7 23. Bxe5+ f6 24. Bxf6+ Qg7 25. Bxg7+ Kxg7 26. h8=Q+ $1 {White has to force the pace, or Black's bishops will be strong.} Rxh8 27. Rxh8 Kxh8 28. Rd1 Bc6 29. Rd8+ Kg7 30. Rc8 Bd5 31. Rc7+ Kf6 32. Rxa7 {with equality!?}) *

