e3}) 17... Rd8 $13 ({Black should avoid} 17... Nxc2 $6 18. Qd7 $1 Nxa1 19. Qxb7 Nc2 20. a3 {when the knight is stuck.}) ({After} 17... Rd8 {one possibility is} 18. Qe5 Bd6 19. Qc3 Bxf4 20. exf4 Qe7 {with the ideas ...Qh4 and ...Nd5. If} 21. Rad1 Nd3 $1 {followed by ...Qh4 gives Black dangerous play. This is all a bit of fantasy, but it gives us some ideas for fighting for the initiative when White gets 'creative' on the kingside.}) *

