1. d4 d5 2. Nf3 Nf6 3. Bg5 {The Torre Attack, in this form, is basically dubious. 1.d4 Nf6 2.Nf3 e6 3.Bg5 is more respectable.} Ne4 ({Part of me wanted to be 'consistent' and offer} 3... e6 {which is not as passive as it appears to be, especially considering pretty much all other courses all give . Black is often fighting for the advantage at an early stage of the game here though. There's a reason everyone recommends this move - there are not many openings where Black is scoring 55%+ in a position after just three moves! Nevertheless, I will give my own take here, and I hope I can offer more power to Black's cause.}) 4. Bf4 {This move is much more sound, although White still needs to be careful.} c5 5. e3 {The main line.} Qb6 {[%mdl 32768]} ({The most ambitious. Both} 5... Nc6 {and}) (5... cxd4 6. exd4 Nc6 {are fine for Black as well.}) 6. b3 $6 {Just like in the 4.Bh4 line, this just makes weaknesses on the queenside.} Nc6 7. c3 cxd4 8. exd4 ({If} 8. cxd4 $2 e5 {followed by ...Bb4+ and ...Bg4, is a disaster for White.}) 8... Bg4 $15 {[%csl Rc3] Black is more active and White has weakened his queenside.} *

