 bxc6 Qxc6 {is a good extra pawn.}) 15... Bd7 16. Nc4 {[%cal Gc7d6,Gc4d6]} (16. Bxc6 Bxc6 17. Ba5 {saves the bishop, but White's position is still terrible after} b6 18. Bb4 Rd8 $17 {when White's knight has no future.}) 16... Nb4 $1 {[%cal Gb4d3,Ga8c8] A convincing move which is quickly indicated by the engines.} (16... Qe6 {is less convincing after} 17. Qd2 {taking control of the d6-square.}) 17. Bxd7+ ({After} 17. cxb4 $2 Bxb5 {White will suffer big losses on the c-file}) 17... Qxd7 18. cxb4 Bxb4+ 19. Nd2 ({Or} 19. Kf1 Qxc7 $17 {with an extra pawn and a better position.}) 19... Rc8 {[%csl Rc7] Black wins back the piece with a winning position.} *

