1. d4 d5 2. Nf3 Nf6 3. Bg5 {The Torre Attack, in this form, is basically dubious. 1.d4 Nf6 2.Nf3 e6 3.Bg5 is more respectable.} Ne4 ({Part of me wanted to be 'consistent' and offer} 3... e6 {which is not as passive as it appears to be, especially considering pretty much all other courses all give . Black is often fighting for the advantage at an early stage of the game here though. There's a reason everyone recommends this move - there are not many openings where Black is scoring 55%+ in a position after just three moves! Nevertheless, I will give my own take here, and I hope I can offer more power to Black's cause.}) 4. Bf4 {This move is much more sound, although White still needs to be careful.} c5 5. e3 {The main line.} Qb6 ({The most ambitious. Both} 5... Nc6 {and}) (5... cxd4 6. exd4 Nc6 {are fine for Black as well.}) 6. Qc1 {By far the most common move, but White has to walk a tightrope.} Nc6 {It's best to maintain the tension. Black is playing for an advantage here.} (6... cxd4 7. exd4 Nc6 8. c3 {is fine too after} Bf5 {or 8...Bg4=}) 7. c3 ({Giving up the center with} 7. dxc5 {is obviously a concession.} Qxc5 8. Nbd2 Nxd2 9. Qxd2 f6 $15 {is a familiar story.}) 7... f6 $5 {[%cal Gg7g5,Gh7h5,Ge7e5] Now ...g5 followed by ...h5 is a real threat, while White also has to be wary of ...e5.} (7... Bf5 {is simple enough, but we can play for more.}) 8. h3 {This looks like the best try to me. White removes the sting of ...g5 by providing a retreat to the bishop. Black thus strikes from the other direction.} cxd4 $1 {White will have to open either the e1-a5 or g1-a7 diagonal.} 9. exd4 e5 $1 {[%csl Rf2][%cal Gb6f2]} 10. Be3 {Everything else loses material.} exd4 11. Nxd4 ({Opening the c-file with} 11. cxd4 {leads to trouble after} Bf5 {and ...Rc8 is coming.}) 11... Bc5 {Many writers have considered this position to be disastrous for White. It's true that it's not very good, but White is more alive than has been indicated.} ({I'll mention that} 11... Nxd4 {is good too, but after} 12. Bxd4 Bc5 13. Bxc5 Qxc5 14. Qe3 {Black is merely comfortable - there is no knockout.}) 12. Be2 ({An untried move, which is better than} 12. Nc2 {or .}) 12... Nxd4 {[%mdl 32768]} 13. cxd4 Bb4+ ({I prefer this to} 13... Bxd4 14. Bxd4 Qxd4 15. O-O {when White has some compensation for the pawn.}) 14. Nc3 Bf5 $15 {[%csl Rc1][%cal Ga8c8,Ge8g8] Black is more active.} *

