1. d4 d5 {Fischer was famous for playing the King's Indian, but in this game he decided to go with the Queen's Gambit Declined for some reason!} 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 Be7 {Fischer uses our preferred move order.} 4. Nf3 Nf6 5. Bg5 O-O ({We will play} 5... h6 {first.}) 6. e3 h6 7. Bh4 b6 8. cxd5 Nxd5 9. Bxe7 Qxe7 10. Nxd5 exd5 11. Be2 {A quiet move.} Be6 $1 12. O-O c5 13. dxc5 bxc5 {[%csl Gc5,Gd5] Hanging pawns. Playing with such a structure used to concern me, but to grow as a player you have to accept that there are good and bad version of almost any pawn formation.} 14. Qa4 Qb7 $5 {[%cal Gb7b2]} ({In the course we will go [/variation/20836186/#/14/b] for} 14... Nd7 {but Fischer's move is good as well.}) 15. Qa3 Nd7 {[%cal Ga7a5] Black is quite comfortable here, as he has clear play on the queenside and White cannot easily pressure the hanging pawns.} 16. Ne1 $6 {[%cal Ge1d3,Gd3f4,Gd3c5] This is not a rare idea, but it's rather slow here.} a5 $1 17. Nd3 c4 $1 {Giving up the d4-square does not mean much here. Our bishop is rather bad, but Black has clear play, while White does not.} 18. Nf4 Rfb8 {[%csl Rb2]} 19. Rab1 $2 ({Bertok probably did not want to take the bad bishop with} 19. Nxe6 {but this may still be the best try.} fxe6 20. b3 $5 {If 20.Bg4 Ra6 Or 20.Qd6 Ra6} cxb3 21. axb3 Qxb3 22. Qd6 Nf8 23. Bg4 {and at least White has some activity.}) 19... Bf5 $1 20. Rbd1 Nf6 {[%csl Rb2]} 21. Rd2 {White has played rather natural moves, but Fischer is very concrete and spots the flaws in any inaccuracy.} g5 {Suddenly White is lost.} 22. Nxd5 {Desperation.} ({If} 22. Nh3) ({(} 22. Nh5 {would be met in the same way)}) 22... Ne4 23. Rc2 Qb4 {and White's position is falling apart. It looks 'bad for White', but the engine has it at a whopping -4! Nxd5} 24. Bxc4 ({Worse is} 24. Bf3 $2 {Bd3!}) 24... Be6 {Black is up a piece for two pawns.} 25. Rd1 $2 {Allowing a shot. Nxe3! Fischer is alert as always. Qxe3 Bxc4 h4} {If Bxe6 taking the rook would win, but Qxg2 looks even better!} Re8 {Qg3 Qe7} 26. b3 {Be6 f4} g4 {h5 Qc5+ Rf2 Bf5} 0-1

